1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,006
The most entertaining suspense
that predicts love.

2
00:00:03,006 --> 00:00:04,716
Love line prediction game, Heart Signal.

3
00:00:04,716 --> 00:00:08,526
Five people with sharp romance
radars have gathered.

4
00:00:08,526 --> 00:00:11,236
[The panel of five people is here]

5
00:00:11,236 --> 00:00:15,136
They left on a trip to Tokushima, Japan,
last week.

6
00:00:15,136 --> 00:00:17,056
It was Heart Signal's first overseas trip.

7
00:00:17,056 --> 00:00:20,536
The first dates in Japan were
arranged by the men.

8
00:00:20,536 --> 00:00:24,216
Seong Min chose Yu Gyeong as his date.

9
00:00:24,216 --> 00:00:27,466
- He did his best.
- He did.

10
00:00:27,466 --> 00:00:29,806
I still can't forget the look in his eyes.

11
00:00:29,806 --> 00:00:32,136
And Jun Hyeon and So Yun's date.

12
00:00:32,136 --> 00:00:34,036
They were kind of sad.

13
00:00:34,036 --> 00:00:37,486
She was most aggressive with Wu Yeol.

14
00:00:37,486 --> 00:00:40,536
- She was like, "Want to talk casually?"
- Right.

15
00:00:40,536 --> 00:00:45,066
But she was so delicate with Jun Hyeon.

16
00:00:45,066 --> 00:00:47,196
Her feelings seemed stronger than we thought.

17
00:00:47,196 --> 00:00:49,836
I was duped by So Yun.

18
00:00:49,836 --> 00:00:52,376
She acted like she was a tough lady.

19
00:00:52,376 --> 00:00:54,466
I thought she'd be so nonchalant,
but she wasn't.

20
00:00:54,466 --> 00:00:57,646
Not at all. And she still thinks
about her first love.

21
00:00:57,646 --> 00:01:01,206
We find her more lovely that way,

22
00:01:01,206 --> 00:01:05,606
but I'm worried since I want her
to win her love there.

23
00:01:05,606 --> 00:01:07,806
And Jun Hyeon was unexpected.

24
00:01:07,806 --> 00:01:10,126
He was like, "I choose Yu Gyeong"
in front of everyone.

25
00:01:10,126 --> 00:01:14,276
I think he'll act like
a true game-changer now.

26
00:01:14,276 --> 00:01:16,396
Wu Yeol and Gyu Ri's date.

27
00:01:16,396 --> 00:01:18,776
Every moment was quite memorable.

28
00:01:18,776 --> 00:01:22,896
It was so intense from start to finish.

29
00:01:22,896 --> 00:01:26,056
There was a subtle mind game going on.

30
00:01:26,056 --> 00:01:30,226
You have to leave possibilities open
and make them curious.

31
00:01:30,226 --> 00:01:33,286
And what they did
was a classic example of that.

32
00:01:33,286 --> 00:01:35,656
Like in "Before Sunset,"

33
00:01:35,656 --> 00:01:40,386
their conversation
intensified the atmosphere.

34
00:01:40,386 --> 00:01:41,926
Will you choose me?

35
00:01:41,926 --> 00:01:44,426
If I have fun tonight.

36
00:01:44,426 --> 00:01:45,996
What a comment.

37
00:01:45,996 --> 00:01:50,256
She declared war by saying that.
She definitely did.

38
00:01:50,256 --> 00:01:52,646
And they picked out socks for each other.

39
00:01:52,646 --> 00:01:54,736
Rather than picking out nice ones,

40
00:01:54,736 --> 00:01:58,356
she picked a very bright color pair
and said, "Wear these."

41
00:01:58,356 --> 00:02:01,316
She picked the ones he wouldn't usually wear.

42
00:02:01,316 --> 00:02:04,106
She challenged him to wear them

43
00:02:04,106 --> 00:02:06,916
so that they could share a secret.

44
00:02:06,916 --> 00:02:10,366
She's curious if he'd wear them
in front of everyone.

45
00:02:10,366 --> 00:02:13,366
- That's it.
- If he does, it will start

46
00:02:13,366 --> 00:02:15,186
a secret conversation between them.

47
00:02:15,186 --> 00:02:19,176
You see this often in idol romances.

48
00:02:19,176 --> 00:02:20,436
I didn't want to bring that up.

49
00:02:20,436 --> 00:02:23,066
They suddenly act out
during an award ceremony.

50
00:02:23,066 --> 00:02:25,626
They suddenly do stuff like this.

51
00:02:25,626 --> 00:02:27,206
- This?
- They signal at someone.

52
00:02:27,206 --> 00:02:30,376
Roy, you undid three buttons.

53
00:02:30,376 --> 00:02:33,256
- Are you signaling at someone?
- It's a bit awkward.

54
00:02:33,256 --> 00:02:35,536
It's awkward. It's open too much.

55
00:02:35,536 --> 00:02:38,346
- What look are you going for?
- Sorry. Don't look.

56
00:02:38,346 --> 00:02:40,036
I'll cover myself up.

57
00:02:40,036 --> 00:02:43,946
And Gyu Ri wanted to see "Once We Were Us."

58
00:02:43,946 --> 00:02:45,206
That was crazy.

59
00:02:45,206 --> 00:02:47,486
I think something serious will happen.

60
00:02:47,486 --> 00:02:49,866
Since they're about a week in,

61
00:02:49,866 --> 00:02:52,926
Gyu Ri is considering staying in one lane.

62
00:02:52,926 --> 00:02:54,466
- It is Day 8.
- I know.

63
00:02:54,466 --> 00:02:58,916
She was like, "Could you stop
playing both sides?"

64
00:02:58,916 --> 00:03:00,836
That could be her intention.

65
00:03:00,836 --> 00:03:03,676
Or saying,
"I'll switch lanes if this won't work."

66
00:03:03,676 --> 00:03:05,006
Why did she choose that movie?

67
00:03:05,006 --> 00:03:07,716
I would've chosen a horror movie.

68
00:03:07,716 --> 00:03:10,026
She could scream, too.

69
00:03:10,026 --> 00:03:12,666
They're having their second dates
in Japan today.

70
00:03:12,666 --> 00:03:16,856
Let's find out
what kinds of dates they'll have.

71
00:03:16,856 --> 00:03:18,026
[The first day in Japan]

72
00:03:18,026 --> 00:03:19,826
Will you choose me?

73
00:03:23,836 --> 00:03:25,286
If I have fun tonight.

74
00:03:25,286 --> 00:03:27,626
[Teasingly, concealing their heart]

75
00:03:27,626 --> 00:03:29,286
A revenge, maybe?

76
00:03:30,546 --> 00:03:34,136
It was like a revenge for the
brown sweater incident.

77
00:03:35,996 --> 00:03:38,346
But regardless of all that,

78
00:03:38,346 --> 00:03:42,056
I strategized for rock, paper,
scissors the next day.

79
00:03:42,056 --> 00:03:43,126
She strategized?

80
00:03:43,126 --> 00:03:46,966
I was like,
"Which one did this person do first?"

81
00:03:46,966 --> 00:03:49,026
She's trying to control her luck.

82
00:03:49,026 --> 00:03:51,586
I was like,

83
00:03:51,586 --> 00:03:56,306
"I didn't get a text. He must've had fun."

84
00:03:56,306 --> 00:03:58,676
But there's nothing I can do.

85
00:03:58,676 --> 00:04:04,046
I wanted to have a date
with Wu Yeol the next day.

86
00:04:04,046 --> 00:04:07,246
Wu Yeol made the strongest first impression.

87
00:04:07,246 --> 00:04:09,846
I wanted to talk to him more while in Japan.

88
00:04:09,846 --> 00:04:13,886
It's a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity,
you know.

89
00:04:13,886 --> 00:04:15,106
I want to know him more.

90
00:04:15,106 --> 00:04:17,496
- So Yun, too?
- It's Wu Yeol again.

91
00:04:17,496 --> 00:04:20,616
[While the emotions whirlpool,]

92
00:04:20,616 --> 00:04:26,376
[the second morning in Japan is here]

93
00:04:28,686 --> 00:04:32,106
- It smells amazing.
- We're in Japan!

94
00:04:33,106 --> 00:04:36,786
- Seriously. I'm hungry.
- There's so much to eat.

95
00:04:36,786 --> 00:04:39,306
- What's that?
- Looks tasty.

96
00:04:40,236 --> 00:04:42,986
Looks so good.

97
00:04:42,986 --> 00:04:46,706
[Choosing what to have for breakfast]

98
00:04:46,706 --> 00:04:48,276
[Looks good]

99
00:04:49,616 --> 00:04:52,396
[Dropping]

100
00:04:52,396 --> 00:04:54,546
There's so much to eat.

101
00:04:54,546 --> 00:04:55,696
[Ta-da]

102
00:04:57,976 --> 00:05:00,766
Cereal.

103
00:05:00,766 --> 00:05:04,056
- This is so cute.
- We're so different.

104
00:05:04,056 --> 00:05:05,926
They're such good friends.

105
00:05:05,926 --> 00:05:07,746
So cute.

106
00:05:07,746 --> 00:05:08,866
One, two...

107
00:05:08,866 --> 00:05:13,146
[Can't skip photos in the morning, either]

108
00:05:13,146 --> 00:05:16,116
So pretty.

109
00:05:16,116 --> 00:05:17,526
Good.

110
00:05:20,026 --> 00:05:21,516
[Mmm]

111
00:05:21,516 --> 00:05:24,106
- They have similar reactions.
- Same wavelength, too.

112
00:05:24,106 --> 00:05:25,676
[So Yun and Gyu Ri arrive]

113
00:05:25,676 --> 00:05:27,476
Hi.

114
00:05:27,476 --> 00:05:29,186
- Hi.
- Wow, so pretty.

115
00:05:29,186 --> 00:05:31,076
Come join us.

116
00:05:31,076 --> 00:05:34,816
Wow, what's all this?

117
00:05:34,816 --> 00:05:36,706
That looks delicious.

118
00:05:36,706 --> 00:05:39,346
You can see the difference in taste.

119
00:05:39,346 --> 00:05:41,156
- I know.
- You went nuts.

120
00:05:41,156 --> 00:05:42,776
- I did go nuts.
- There's so much.

121
00:05:42,776 --> 00:05:45,626
What direction should I go?

122
00:05:45,626 --> 00:05:48,536
Just eat whatever you want. There's so much.

123
00:05:48,536 --> 00:05:50,936
She seems uncomfortable.

124
00:05:51,886 --> 00:05:55,826
[They seem slightly awkward]

125
00:05:55,826 --> 00:05:59,586
The salad is crazy. It's delicious.

126
00:06:04,266 --> 00:06:06,506
You guys aren't eating much.

127
00:06:08,226 --> 00:06:10,576
Thanks for the meal.

128
00:06:10,576 --> 00:06:12,756
Gyu Ri is in a good mood.

129
00:06:12,756 --> 00:06:15,626
How could she be so transparent?

130
00:06:19,686 --> 00:06:21,316
[Uncomfortable]

131
00:06:21,316 --> 00:06:23,896
- Did you sleep well?
- Yes.

132
00:06:23,896 --> 00:06:26,216
I slept well.

133
00:06:26,216 --> 00:06:27,426
What did you do?

134
00:06:27,426 --> 00:06:32,376
Did you eat? Weren't you full already?

135
00:06:33,556 --> 00:06:37,946
Because I wanted to have a date

136
00:06:37,946 --> 00:06:42,826
with alcohol and food,

137
00:06:42,826 --> 00:06:46,386
I didn't eat a lot of sea bream.

138
00:06:46,386 --> 00:06:48,866
Wow, so strategic.

139
00:06:48,866 --> 00:06:50,416
Right, she is.

140
00:06:50,416 --> 00:06:52,256
I'm a strategic type.

141
00:06:53,256 --> 00:06:55,356
The date was fun.

142
00:06:57,756 --> 00:06:59,996
- Isn't Gyu Ri so confident right now?
- I know.

143
00:06:59,996 --> 00:07:02,486
Yu Gyeong asked what they did.

144
00:07:02,486 --> 00:07:05,686
But her answer is "It was nice."
That's important.

145
00:07:05,686 --> 00:07:07,406
She said that directly to Yu Gyeong.

146
00:07:07,406 --> 00:07:10,106
She had to pretend yesterday was amazing

147
00:07:10,106 --> 00:07:12,966
to make her imagine,
even though not much happened.

148
00:07:12,966 --> 00:07:16,006
- She's trying to overpower her.
- Absolutely.

149
00:07:16,006 --> 00:07:18,676
I was most curious about the night view.

150
00:07:18,676 --> 00:07:21,036
Was it nice? Did you go somewhere
with a nice view?

151
00:07:21,036 --> 00:07:22,576
We didn't expect much.

152
00:07:22,576 --> 00:07:26,796
But as soon as we went up, we went, "Wow."

153
00:07:26,796 --> 00:07:31,216
It was so pretty. It was different
than the night view in Seoul.

154
00:07:31,216 --> 00:07:35,686
We talked about our ideal types and...

155
00:07:35,686 --> 00:07:37,336
- Hi.
- Were you eating?

156
00:07:37,336 --> 00:07:40,026
- Good morning.
- Hi.

157
00:07:40,026 --> 00:07:41,606
- Good morning.
- Did you sleep well?

158
00:07:41,606 --> 00:07:43,276
Good morning, everyone.

159
00:07:43,276 --> 00:07:46,786
- You were eating.
- We were.

160
00:07:46,786 --> 00:07:49,176
Did you all sleep well?

161
00:07:49,176 --> 00:07:52,396
I blacked out as soon as I lay down.

162
00:07:53,686 --> 00:07:54,886
[Turning]

163
00:07:54,886 --> 00:07:56,016
[Turning]

164
00:07:58,366 --> 00:08:01,686
[Things are getting tense between the women]

165
00:08:03,626 --> 00:08:05,156
What?

166
00:08:06,156 --> 00:08:08,056
Should we...

167
00:08:09,146 --> 00:08:11,506
Should we reveal our picks
when you're back with food?

168
00:08:11,506 --> 00:08:13,436
What?

169
00:08:13,436 --> 00:08:16,066
[Revealing the dates to start the morning]

170
00:08:16,066 --> 00:08:18,896
From behind? Guess who.

171
00:08:19,936 --> 00:08:21,206
[Flustered]

172
00:08:21,206 --> 00:08:23,296
Seriously? Did you pick one each?

173
00:08:23,296 --> 00:08:26,166
Let's discuss after we eat.

174
00:08:26,166 --> 00:08:28,666
- They won't be able to.
- I can't eat, then.

175
00:08:28,666 --> 00:08:31,406
- I'm wide awake.
- What are those?

176
00:08:31,406 --> 00:08:33,576
What are they?

177
00:08:33,576 --> 00:08:35,036
It must be like a pass.

178
00:08:35,036 --> 00:08:37,006
- Names are written down.
- They're all different.

179
00:08:37,006 --> 00:08:38,256
Travel itineraries.

180
00:08:38,256 --> 00:08:41,006
[The pamphlets with today's travel itinerary]

181
00:08:41,006 --> 00:08:44,736
Choose the itinerary you like.
We'll go along with it.

182
00:08:44,736 --> 00:08:49,936
Would you like to choose one
you like or choose randomly?

183
00:08:49,936 --> 00:08:51,896
Let's have a look first.

184
00:08:53,696 --> 00:08:57,016
- Gosh, I want to go here.
- I want to go here.

185
00:08:57,016 --> 00:08:59,096
Studio Ghibli vibe?

186
00:08:59,096 --> 00:09:01,426
A train ride is a must, isn't it?

187
00:09:01,426 --> 00:09:05,126
- Do we get to bike, too?
- They need a bit of luck, too.

188
00:09:05,126 --> 00:09:08,136
- How about we...
- Let's eat.

189
00:09:08,136 --> 00:09:10,936
Can we eat over there instead?

190
00:09:10,936 --> 00:09:12,806
- What's the deal?
- Where do I begin?

191
00:09:12,806 --> 00:09:15,096
[After the men leave]

192
00:09:15,096 --> 00:09:17,646
This is like braised beef.

193
00:09:17,646 --> 00:09:19,386
So tense. So tense.

194
00:09:19,386 --> 00:09:22,436
Let's just do rock, paper, scissors.

195
00:09:22,436 --> 00:09:24,476
- Clean and simple.
- She practiced last night.

196
00:09:24,476 --> 00:09:28,476
- Whoever wins...
- Gets to choose first.

197
00:09:28,476 --> 00:09:30,956
[Their date depends on this game]

198
00:09:30,956 --> 00:09:33,996
Play or lose, rock, paper, scissors.

199
00:09:33,996 --> 00:09:35,636
Rock, paper, scissors. Rock, paper, scissors.

200
00:09:35,636 --> 00:09:37,026
[Yu Gyeong loses]

201
00:09:37,026 --> 00:09:39,116
She lost.

202
00:09:41,336 --> 00:09:42,556
[Glancing]

203
00:09:43,066 --> 00:09:44,836
Rock, paper, scissors.

204
00:09:44,836 --> 00:09:46,816
[Gyu Ri loses in the second round]

205
00:09:46,816 --> 00:09:48,636
Rock, paper, scissors. Rock, paper, scissors.

206
00:09:48,636 --> 00:09:50,146
[So Yun is the final winner]

207
00:09:50,146 --> 00:09:53,106
So, I get to choose?

208
00:09:53,106 --> 00:09:54,246
[Disappointed]

209
00:09:54,246 --> 00:09:55,956
She's disappointed.

210
00:09:59,006 --> 00:10:01,756
[So Yun got her chance]

211
00:10:01,756 --> 00:10:03,726
- Wow.
- So Yun.

212
00:10:03,726 --> 00:10:05,056
She might choose Jun Hyeon.

213
00:10:05,056 --> 00:10:07,956
- She'll choose Wu Yeol.
- Choose Wu Yeol.

214
00:10:07,956 --> 00:10:10,586
- Seriously.
- It's on another level.

215
00:10:10,586 --> 00:10:12,116
On another level.

216
00:10:12,116 --> 00:10:14,746
- Have you decided?
- Yes.

217
00:10:14,746 --> 00:10:16,486
How did you decide?

218
00:10:16,486 --> 00:10:17,726
It's a secret.

219
00:10:17,726 --> 00:10:19,996
[What decisions did they make?]

220
00:10:20,696 --> 00:10:21,606
[Shutting his eyes]

221
00:10:21,606 --> 00:10:25,276
He's waiting. He's waiting.

222
00:10:25,276 --> 00:10:27,386
Who is it?

223
00:10:29,336 --> 00:10:33,136
- Gosh, how do I say it?
- Should we just say it?

224
00:10:33,136 --> 00:10:35,776
Should we take turns to reveal?

225
00:10:35,776 --> 00:10:38,246
Say, "The one going on a date
with me today is..."?

226
00:10:38,246 --> 00:10:40,246
Sounds good.

227
00:10:42,366 --> 00:10:44,156
[Glancing]

228
00:10:48,496 --> 00:10:50,956
They must be so nervous.

229
00:10:52,846 --> 00:10:54,736
Seong Min.

230
00:10:54,736 --> 00:10:56,236
[Min Ju chose Seong Min as her date]

231
00:10:56,236 --> 00:10:58,566
- Min Ju is forging ahead, too.
- Tokushima.

232
00:10:58,566 --> 00:11:00,946
It's our itinerary.

233
00:11:02,226 --> 00:11:04,336
You scared me. You shoved it in.

234
00:11:04,336 --> 00:11:06,046
[Embarrassed]

235
00:11:07,986 --> 00:11:10,186
- Sounds good.
- Oh, yeah?

236
00:11:12,546 --> 00:11:13,736
[It's Gyu Ri's turn]

237
00:11:13,736 --> 00:11:15,506
I'm so curious.

238
00:11:19,656 --> 00:11:20,906
[Thinking]

239
00:11:22,976 --> 00:11:24,316
Should I just go?

240
00:11:24,316 --> 00:11:26,796
[The two men are nervous]

241
00:11:29,436 --> 00:11:30,906
Join me.

242
00:11:30,906 --> 00:11:34,336
- It was Seo Won.
- Miyoshi?

243
00:11:34,336 --> 00:11:37,206
Seo Won must be thrilled.

244
00:11:40,696 --> 00:11:43,896
[Disappointed]

245
00:11:46,246 --> 00:11:48,396
[Feeling conflicted]

246
00:11:52,566 --> 00:11:54,816
Wu Yeol. Wu Yeol.

247
00:11:54,816 --> 00:11:57,146
Mima?

248
00:11:58,306 --> 00:11:59,916
Yu Gyeong's date is Jun Hyeon?

249
00:11:59,916 --> 00:12:02,166
Join me.

250
00:12:02,166 --> 00:12:04,076
Naruto? Naruto?

251
00:12:04,076 --> 00:12:05,426
Sounds good, right? Read it.

252
00:12:05,426 --> 00:12:07,106
Jun Hyeon got lucky.

253
00:12:07,106 --> 00:12:10,056
Wow, I love this. The dye factory.

254
00:12:10,056 --> 00:12:13,286
Dye factory? That's why I chose that one.

255
00:12:14,856 --> 00:12:18,206
- Making handkerchiefs and scarves.
- It bothers her.

256
00:12:18,206 --> 00:12:19,616
We won't race on the bikes, right?

257
00:12:19,616 --> 00:12:21,466
- Do you like to bike?
- Yes.

258
00:12:21,466 --> 00:12:22,606
[Yay]

259
00:12:22,606 --> 00:12:23,816
So cute.

260
00:12:23,816 --> 00:12:27,176
- Naruto is the best.
- I like Naruto the best.

261
00:12:27,176 --> 00:12:29,866
- Where's Naruto?
- I'm going to Miyoshi.

262
00:12:29,866 --> 00:12:31,836
Wasn't this one popular?

263
00:12:31,836 --> 00:12:36,676
- I wanted to ride on a train.
- Oh, train?

264
00:12:36,676 --> 00:12:38,886
- I don't like trains.
- Good conversationalist.

265
00:12:38,886 --> 00:12:41,566
Let's visit the suspension bridge, then.

266
00:12:41,566 --> 00:12:43,756
I like suspense.

267
00:12:44,586 --> 00:12:48,416
- You're serious.
- I've been shaking my legs.

268
00:12:48,416 --> 00:12:49,436
[Excited]

269
00:12:50,716 --> 00:12:51,936
[Bothered]

270
00:12:51,936 --> 00:12:54,276
- Wu Yeol is disappointed.
- He doesn't look happy.

271
00:12:54,276 --> 00:12:57,086
Should we bring the stuff we need?

272
00:12:57,086 --> 00:13:00,946
Let's pack and go.

273
00:13:00,946 --> 00:13:02,996
- Do you have to go back?
- Where?

274
00:13:02,996 --> 00:13:05,236
- The room.
- No, I brought everything.

275
00:13:05,236 --> 00:13:07,216
Should we go, too?

276
00:13:07,216 --> 00:13:09,776
We should bring something. Water, at least.

277
00:13:09,776 --> 00:13:11,616
[Hesitating]

278
00:13:13,236 --> 00:13:15,106
Just stay here, then.

279
00:13:15,106 --> 00:13:23,116
[What emotions will today's choices bring?]

280
00:13:23,116 --> 00:13:25,366
- Wow.
- I'm so curious.

281
00:13:25,366 --> 00:13:26,796
Did you notice it?

282
00:13:26,796 --> 00:13:29,236
Gyu Ri lurked around Wu Yeol while leaving.

283
00:13:29,236 --> 00:13:31,346
But that's just her habit.

284
00:13:31,346 --> 00:13:33,376
She lurks by habit?

285
00:13:33,376 --> 00:13:35,346
She always lurks around Wu Yeol.

286
00:13:35,346 --> 00:13:36,886
Lurk Around Wu Yeol Syndrome.

287
00:13:36,886 --> 00:13:40,296
She tries hard to get his attention.

288
00:13:40,296 --> 00:13:41,876
Instead of lurking,

289
00:13:41,876 --> 00:13:44,516
she should try fainting.

290
00:13:44,516 --> 00:13:46,106
This isn't a soap opera.

291
00:13:46,106 --> 00:13:48,176
Jong Shin is feeling good today.

292
00:13:48,176 --> 00:13:49,156
[Proud]

293
00:13:49,156 --> 00:13:52,496
And by winning rock, paper, scissors,
So Yun...

294
00:13:52,496 --> 00:13:54,016
So Yun won first place.

295
00:13:54,016 --> 00:13:56,826
If Jun Hyeon was nice and
hinted at the possibility,

296
00:13:56,826 --> 00:13:59,436
- she could've chosen Jun Hyeon.
- Right.

297
00:13:59,436 --> 00:14:02,336
But she didn't because he's determined.

298
00:14:02,336 --> 00:14:03,986
You're right. You're right.

299
00:14:03,986 --> 00:14:06,776
Good work, Jun Hyeon.

300
00:14:06,776 --> 00:14:10,166
I'm loving these pairings.

301
00:14:15,386 --> 00:14:17,256
I have to get the door.

302
00:14:17,256 --> 00:14:19,936
- What's this?
- It opened automatically.

303
00:14:19,936 --> 00:14:23,206
- It took my job.
- Thank you.

304
00:14:26,036 --> 00:14:29,066
We have to go all out since
we're leaving tomorrow, okay?

305
00:14:29,066 --> 00:14:31,686
- Let's play hard.
- I'm not sleeping tonight.

306
00:14:33,006 --> 00:14:35,406
It will be so fun. I'm so excited right now.

307
00:14:35,406 --> 00:14:36,756
Want a selfie?

308
00:14:37,706 --> 00:14:39,176
[Selfie time on the way]

309
00:14:39,176 --> 00:14:42,366
- You saw it going straight, right?
- Yes.

310
00:14:42,366 --> 00:14:43,366
[Click]

311
00:14:43,366 --> 00:14:44,336
So fun.

312
00:14:44,336 --> 00:14:45,346
[Full of excitement]

313
00:14:45,346 --> 00:14:47,006
Did you say you've been to Japan?

314
00:14:47,006 --> 00:14:49,976
I've only been to Tokyo and Osaka.

315
00:14:49,976 --> 00:14:53,936
I prefer the countryside to cities.
A place like this.

316
00:14:53,936 --> 00:14:56,286
I haven't been to a place like this.

317
00:14:56,286 --> 00:14:59,046
I've never experienced a place like this.

318
00:15:00,786 --> 00:15:03,366
Have you been on a date with Yu Gyeong?

319
00:15:03,366 --> 00:15:05,056
What? All of a sudden?

320
00:15:05,056 --> 00:15:06,326
Yesterday.

321
00:15:06,326 --> 00:15:08,816
- Yesterday.
- Right, right.

322
00:15:09,596 --> 00:15:11,156
You're right.

323
00:15:13,736 --> 00:15:16,006
[Last night, while drinking]

324
00:15:16,006 --> 00:15:17,636
Did I go too fast?

325
00:15:17,636 --> 00:15:19,256
- No, no.
- It was cool.

326
00:15:19,256 --> 00:15:22,016
You stepped up, so I went for it, too.

327
00:15:22,016 --> 00:15:24,256
Two people who went fast.

328
00:15:24,256 --> 00:15:27,526
We played rock, paper, scissors earlier.

329
00:15:27,526 --> 00:15:29,776
[Min Ju was the only one who couldn't laugh]

330
00:15:29,776 --> 00:15:31,686
[And this morning]

331
00:15:31,686 --> 00:15:33,566
[Glancing]

332
00:15:33,566 --> 00:15:35,906
Did you sleep well last night?

333
00:15:35,906 --> 00:15:38,226
Did you all sleep better last night?

334
00:15:38,226 --> 00:15:41,766
[She's bothered by even casual conversations]

335
00:15:44,516 --> 00:15:46,936
Seong Min.

336
00:15:46,936 --> 00:15:49,116
- Oh...
- After all that?

337
00:15:49,116 --> 00:15:51,266
I know. She's still tiptoeing around him.

338
00:15:51,266 --> 00:15:53,146
It's our itinerary.

339
00:15:53,146 --> 00:15:55,826
[Checking his reaction]

340
00:15:56,636 --> 00:15:58,856
- Sounds good.
- Oh, yeah?

341
00:16:02,716 --> 00:16:05,256
She sacrificed her pride and asked him out.

342
00:16:05,256 --> 00:16:08,756
[It took more courage to ask him this time]

343
00:16:10,926 --> 00:16:14,856
[What kind of day
will her courage bring today?]

344
00:16:17,386 --> 00:16:18,746
[Smiling]

345
00:16:18,746 --> 00:16:19,796
Can you sense something?

346
00:16:19,796 --> 00:16:23,086
Yes, it feels so cool. Roll down the window.

347
00:16:23,086 --> 00:16:25,626
- Wow.
- Feels nice, right?

348
00:16:27,076 --> 00:16:28,896
So cute.

349
00:16:32,776 --> 00:16:34,936
[Arrived in downtown Tokushima]

350
00:16:34,936 --> 00:16:37,446
It's a really small town.

351
00:16:37,446 --> 00:16:40,946
Let's just go into random places.

352
00:16:40,946 --> 00:16:43,356
We need to enjoy the moment.

353
00:16:43,356 --> 00:16:45,196
You're right.

354
00:16:45,196 --> 00:16:47,456
This is so nice, too.

355
00:16:47,456 --> 00:16:51,306
Is this the vibe? It's so...

356
00:16:51,306 --> 00:16:54,606
- This is the best.
- I know. It's so nice here, too.

357
00:16:54,606 --> 00:16:56,496
- That...
- Vending machine?

358
00:16:56,496 --> 00:16:58,396
We should take a photo in front
of a vending machine.

359
00:16:58,396 --> 00:17:00,176
- Yes.
- Right? We must.

360
00:17:00,176 --> 00:17:04,196
- I'll pull up my references.
- References...

361
00:17:05,496 --> 00:17:07,166
How nice.

362
00:17:07,166 --> 00:17:09,096
- It's a vending machine, Oppa.
- A vending machine.

363
00:17:09,096 --> 00:17:11,316
We have to. We have to.

364
00:17:11,316 --> 00:17:14,676
You can go forward more.

365
00:17:16,496 --> 00:17:17,816
This is crazy. Hold on. Hold on.

366
00:17:17,816 --> 00:17:21,166
- Does it look good?
- It looks amazing.

367
00:17:21,166 --> 00:17:22,806
[Excited]

368
00:17:22,806 --> 00:17:24,946
- Do you not like it?
- Oppa.

369
00:17:26,336 --> 00:17:27,856
- Not bad, right?
- You did great.

370
00:17:27,856 --> 00:17:30,146
- You like the vibe?
- You're an amazing photographer.

371
00:17:30,146 --> 00:17:32,026
It's because you're pretty.

372
00:17:32,026 --> 00:17:33,466
[Did you call me?]

373
00:17:33,466 --> 00:17:35,096
I got it.

374
00:17:35,096 --> 00:17:37,936
- Gosh.
- Aren't I amazing?

375
00:17:37,936 --> 00:17:39,706
You look 2 meters tall here.

376
00:17:39,706 --> 00:17:41,206
Wu Yeol is nothing in comparison.

377
00:17:41,206 --> 00:17:44,746
Wu Yeol is nothing?
Wow, it turned out so nicely.

378
00:17:44,746 --> 00:17:46,596
You look pretty. I mean it.

379
00:17:46,596 --> 00:17:49,926
- Let me fix this for you.
- Done?

380
00:17:49,926 --> 00:17:53,176
- I think plaid patterns look good on you.
- Really?

381
00:17:53,176 --> 00:17:56,236
- It feels refreshing.
- Really?

382
00:17:56,236 --> 00:17:58,046
Nice to meet you.

383
00:18:00,226 --> 00:18:02,556
Come a little this way.

384
00:18:02,556 --> 00:18:05,786
It looks nice now. It's natural.

385
00:18:07,176 --> 00:18:08,336
[Travel vibe]

386
00:18:08,336 --> 00:18:12,336
This is it. Look to the side like this.

387
00:18:12,336 --> 00:18:14,506
- Nice, nice.
- She's very pretty today.

388
00:18:14,506 --> 00:18:16,026
Try ice this time.

389
00:18:16,026 --> 00:18:17,186
- What's that?
- Ice queen mode.

390
00:18:17,186 --> 00:18:19,086
[Ice queen mode]

391
00:18:19,086 --> 00:18:21,096
Ice queen mode.

392
00:18:22,936 --> 00:18:25,316
- Nice, nice.
- Try doing this again.

393
00:18:25,316 --> 00:18:26,946
What are you doing?

394
00:18:26,946 --> 00:18:30,306
- How do you do that?
- Giggle. Giggle, you know.

395
00:18:32,356 --> 00:18:35,486
I got it. Look, you look amazing.

396
00:18:35,486 --> 00:18:37,866
Laughing naturally like this.

397
00:18:37,866 --> 00:18:39,716
- Giggly.
- You're right.

398
00:18:39,716 --> 00:18:41,856
- A true giggle.
- I love it.

399
00:18:45,056 --> 00:18:47,056
Try this.

400
00:18:47,056 --> 00:18:49,346
Try the cone.

401
00:18:51,086 --> 00:18:52,266
- Sorry.
- It's okay.

402
00:18:52,266 --> 00:18:53,316
[Got ice cream on her hair]

403
00:18:55,426 --> 00:18:56,916
[Hehe]

404
00:18:57,846 --> 00:19:00,366
- Is it on your hair, too?
- Yes.

405
00:19:00,366 --> 00:19:02,236
[Getting closer]

406
00:19:05,066 --> 00:19:08,016
- I'm embarrassed.
- My heart fluttered just now.

407
00:19:14,926 --> 00:19:16,746
[Glancing]

408
00:19:21,476 --> 00:19:23,516
- Shall we?
- Yes.

409
00:19:24,956 --> 00:19:27,436
[Oh!]

410
00:19:29,106 --> 00:19:31,346
Why is it so cute?

411
00:19:31,346 --> 00:19:33,666
I know, it's tiny.

412
00:19:33,666 --> 00:19:37,676
- The view is so romantic.
- Right? It's so nice.

413
00:19:41,646 --> 00:19:44,166
- I won't be able to forget this.
- Right.

414
00:19:45,256 --> 00:19:47,586
I'll act pretty, too.

415
00:19:47,586 --> 00:19:49,746
[Hehe]

416
00:19:49,746 --> 00:19:52,396
It might not be...

417
00:19:52,396 --> 00:19:54,956
Daebak, right? Looks great, right?

418
00:19:54,956 --> 00:19:56,996
- Do you see it?
- I do.

419
00:19:57,886 --> 00:20:03,156
Do you have thoughts to sort out
since you came here?

420
00:20:03,156 --> 00:20:07,066
- I do that in a diary every day.
- Really?

421
00:20:07,876 --> 00:20:09,266
How about you?

422
00:20:10,336 --> 00:20:13,426
- I think things became simpler.
- They did?

423
00:20:15,266 --> 00:20:18,056
Are you pressing the brakes on your emotions?

424
00:20:20,586 --> 00:20:22,456
- Yes.
- Oh, really?

425
00:20:22,456 --> 00:20:24,446
My gosh.

426
00:20:27,666 --> 00:20:30,906
It's prettier here, isn't it?

427
00:20:30,906 --> 00:20:32,986
Should we take one here?

428
00:20:32,986 --> 00:20:37,136
[Immortalizing the moments with photos]

429
00:20:37,136 --> 00:20:38,636
Who's this? Next one.

430
00:20:38,636 --> 00:20:40,316
This one's nice.

431
00:20:41,026 --> 00:20:44,736
The smiley one is nice.
When did you take that?

432
00:20:44,736 --> 00:20:46,056
[Click]

433
00:20:46,056 --> 00:20:46,956
[Pretending he didn't]

434
00:20:46,956 --> 00:20:49,166
Your turn. Your turn.

435
00:20:49,166 --> 00:20:52,926
[Min Ju from Seong Min's perspective]

436
00:20:56,196 --> 00:20:58,926
I love the atmosphere.

437
00:20:58,926 --> 00:21:01,056
[A coffee shop in Tokushima Station]

438
00:21:01,056 --> 00:21:02,926
This is a painting of this.

439
00:21:02,926 --> 00:21:05,276
- You're right.
- Right?

440
00:21:05,276 --> 00:21:08,466
- It's the owner.
- I know. She looks kind of...

441
00:21:08,466 --> 00:21:11,046
Her hairstyle stayed the same.

442
00:21:11,046 --> 00:21:13,526
Is this place 50 years old or something?

443
00:21:13,526 --> 00:21:16,056
I think it might be.

444
00:21:16,056 --> 00:21:20,296
- I think she took these photos.
- It feels kind of...

445
00:21:20,296 --> 00:21:22,466
It's like a Japanese...

446
00:21:27,106 --> 00:21:30,336
Daebak. It's fascinating.

447
00:21:30,336 --> 00:21:33,196
Wow, cheesecake.

448
00:21:33,196 --> 00:21:36,306
- Milk.
- Syrup.

449
00:21:36,306 --> 00:21:37,946
Sugar.

450
00:21:37,946 --> 00:21:40,026
Gosh, so pretty.

451
00:21:40,906 --> 00:21:42,816
[A dessert set with an antique vibe]

452
00:21:42,816 --> 00:21:44,606
I'm curious.

453
00:21:46,256 --> 00:21:48,216
How is it?

454
00:21:48,216 --> 00:21:50,216
Wow, so strong.

455
00:21:51,646 --> 00:21:53,436
It's like a yogurt.

456
00:21:53,436 --> 00:21:54,536
[Yum]

457
00:21:55,315 --> 00:21:57,746
It's good to dip it.
I think you're supposed to.

458
00:21:57,746 --> 00:22:00,606
It's tart and sweet.

459
00:22:05,896 --> 00:22:06,936
[Staring]

460
00:22:06,936 --> 00:22:09,636
- You put your hair behind your ear.
- Why do you ask?

461
00:22:10,616 --> 00:22:11,956
Is this an important moment?

462
00:22:11,956 --> 00:22:15,596
Is it? Is that how it works now?

463
00:22:15,596 --> 00:22:17,096
Is it a sign?

464
00:22:17,096 --> 00:22:20,086
[Concerned]

465
00:22:21,086 --> 00:22:23,876
I find everyone difficult to read.

466
00:22:25,356 --> 00:22:28,276
Everything is unpredictable.
I'm trying to guess,

467
00:22:28,276 --> 00:22:31,606
- but I haven't been right.
- They can't tell what's going on.

468
00:22:31,606 --> 00:22:35,556
I talked to Yu Gyeong
for the first time yesterday.

469
00:22:35,556 --> 00:22:37,746
He's bringing up Yu Gyeong first.

470
00:22:37,746 --> 00:22:41,486
I never got a chance to before.

471
00:22:41,486 --> 00:22:43,816
You went after her immediately.

472
00:22:45,916 --> 00:22:47,386
[Laughing]

473
00:22:56,556 --> 00:22:59,916
I have no confidence in myself.

474
00:22:59,916 --> 00:23:02,306
Why? What do you mean by that?

475
00:23:02,306 --> 00:23:04,856
[Hesitating]

476
00:23:04,856 --> 00:23:09,456
Our dates were determined by...

477
00:23:09,456 --> 00:23:12,216
I wanted to choose you from the beginning.

478
00:23:12,216 --> 00:23:19,286
But I wondered
if I should choose someone else.

479
00:23:19,286 --> 00:23:21,666
[This morning]

480
00:23:21,666 --> 00:23:23,416
Why? Why?

481
00:23:23,416 --> 00:23:26,376
[She was bothered by Seong Min and Yu Gyeong]

482
00:23:26,376 --> 00:23:28,726
Of course, she was.

483
00:23:28,726 --> 00:23:36,076
I dug through my feelings to find out why.

484
00:23:36,076 --> 00:23:41,046
I think it's because I don't trust
myself deep down.

485
00:23:41,046 --> 00:23:43,046
Not confident.

486
00:23:43,046 --> 00:23:47,506
I have no confidence
in changing someone's mind.

487
00:23:47,506 --> 00:23:52,386
Because of that, I kind of...

488
00:23:52,386 --> 00:23:54,426
What do we do?

489
00:23:56,486 --> 00:23:58,486
That's how I feel.

490
00:23:59,966 --> 00:24:04,866
But I'm so happy that I got
to have a date with you.

491
00:24:04,866 --> 00:24:07,196
I was so happy.

492
00:24:07,196 --> 00:24:09,226
Me, too. I'm happy, too.

493
00:24:15,576 --> 00:24:18,476
I'm not sure. I think...

494
00:24:27,156 --> 00:24:28,376
[Fidgeting]

495
00:24:38,426 --> 00:24:39,696
[Slurping]

496
00:24:39,696 --> 00:24:43,686
Feel free. Feel free. Always feel free.

497
00:24:46,376 --> 00:24:49,526
Have you dated someone you like more?

498
00:24:49,526 --> 00:24:52,276
Or have you dated someone...

499
00:24:53,816 --> 00:24:55,976
who likes you more?

500
00:24:55,976 --> 00:24:58,676
Or has he experienced both?

501
00:24:58,676 --> 00:25:02,316
My first relationship was
with someone I liked more.

502
00:25:02,316 --> 00:25:06,396
The second one was the other way around.

503
00:25:07,616 --> 00:25:10,046
But my feelings outgrew hers.

504
00:25:11,216 --> 00:25:13,286
[Hmm]

505
00:25:15,296 --> 00:25:18,586
I think your feelings grow stronger that way.

506
00:25:18,586 --> 00:25:21,596
[Nodding]

507
00:25:21,596 --> 00:25:24,446
[Remembering a particular moment]

508
00:25:25,686 --> 00:25:28,006
- Hi.
- Hi, hello.

509
00:25:28,006 --> 00:25:30,496
- Hello.
- Hello.

510
00:25:30,496 --> 00:25:33,316
- We're about to cook.
- Is no one home?

511
00:25:33,316 --> 00:25:35,116
How much?

512
00:25:35,116 --> 00:25:36,676
A little more?

513
00:25:36,676 --> 00:25:39,446
- A little more.
- A tiny bit more.

514
00:25:39,446 --> 00:25:42,506
I think you're too generous...

515
00:25:42,506 --> 00:25:44,496
[Happy feelings didn't last]

516
00:25:47,146 --> 00:25:49,866
[They're together, but she feels alone]

517
00:25:49,866 --> 00:25:51,886
Squint your eyes and look.

518
00:25:54,206 --> 00:25:55,586
[Turning around]

519
00:25:57,836 --> 00:25:59,386
A teaspoon.

520
00:26:00,846 --> 00:26:02,256
Nice.

521
00:26:04,876 --> 00:26:06,726
No scallions.

522
00:26:08,236 --> 00:26:11,696
[Thinking]

523
00:26:12,336 --> 00:26:14,856
I'll study for a bit.

524
00:26:14,856 --> 00:26:16,666
- Study?
- Study?

525
00:26:16,666 --> 00:26:19,946
