- I just walk.

784
00:40:50,356 --> 00:40:51,546
[Perfect weather for walking together]

785
00:40:51,546 --> 00:40:54,306
It's not too cold. It's perfect.

786
00:40:54,306 --> 00:40:56,236
We'll end up in Seoul at this rate.

787
00:40:56,236 --> 00:40:59,646
- I got hungry.
- It's because we walked.

788
00:41:01,026 --> 00:41:05,806
[They arrived at their destination on foot]

789
00:41:05,806 --> 00:41:07,806
Wow, what's that place?

790
00:41:07,806 --> 00:41:13,916
[An Italian restaurant]

791
00:41:17,636 --> 00:41:20,386
[Course menu]

792
00:41:20,386 --> 00:41:23,276
I don't know much about stuff like this.

793
00:41:23,276 --> 00:41:24,976
What's "dolce"? Dolce.

794
00:41:24,976 --> 00:41:28,476
Dolce means something sweet. Like a dessert.

795
00:41:28,476 --> 00:41:30,596
He knows Italian.

796
00:41:32,246 --> 00:41:35,816
- Fish or meat.
- Really?

797
00:41:35,816 --> 00:41:38,686
- What language is this?
- Italian.

798
00:41:38,686 --> 00:41:40,466
- Daebak.
- So cool.

799
00:41:40,466 --> 00:41:42,776
Hold on. I need to practice.

800
00:41:44,076 --> 00:41:46,226
Try it.

801
00:41:46,226 --> 00:41:47,446
Like this.

802
00:41:47,446 --> 00:41:50,436
Do you have an unusual ideal type?

803
00:41:50,436 --> 00:41:52,376
Unusual ideal type?

804
00:41:52,376 --> 00:41:53,906
Are you good with chopsticks?

805
00:41:53,906 --> 00:41:56,856
- I was going to say that!
- Really? Are you good with chopsticks?

806
00:41:56,856 --> 00:41:57,966
[Someone good with chopsticks]

807
00:41:57,966 --> 00:42:01,406
Like this. Isn't this the proper way?

808
00:42:01,406 --> 00:42:04,246
[Nodding]

809
00:42:04,246 --> 00:42:06,696
[Goofing]

810
00:42:07,626 --> 00:42:08,976
Gosh, so cute.

811
00:42:08,976 --> 00:42:10,956
You're good.

812
00:42:11,956 --> 00:42:13,306
[Haha]

813
00:42:14,376 --> 00:42:18,196
I like someone who is good with chopsticks.

814
00:42:18,196 --> 00:42:21,436
But I can't be bad after saying that.

815
00:42:21,436 --> 00:42:23,726
It wouldn't make sense.

816
00:42:23,726 --> 00:42:26,796
That'd make you judgmental.

817
00:42:26,796 --> 00:42:28,566
- It's true.
- It is.

818
00:42:28,566 --> 00:42:31,476
That's why I practice.

819
00:42:32,416 --> 00:42:35,336
[The first dish is here]

820
00:42:36,196 --> 00:42:38,206
[Eyes widened]

821
00:42:39,606 --> 00:42:42,756
Wow, daebak.

822
00:42:42,756 --> 00:42:46,156
They plated it so prettily.

823
00:42:50,326 --> 00:42:54,116
She frowns when something is delicious.

824
00:42:54,116 --> 00:42:56,256
Isn't the sauce tasty?

825
00:42:57,216 --> 00:42:59,276
So tasty.

826
00:43:00,276 --> 00:43:02,456
I'm so happy.

827
00:43:02,456 --> 00:43:05,476
We came to a really good place.

828
00:43:09,506 --> 00:43:13,176
I don't eat sashimi, but I've
worked at a sashimi restaurant.

829
00:43:13,176 --> 00:43:17,076
- Doing serving?
- Yes. A Japanese restaurant.

830
00:43:17,076 --> 00:43:19,846
This is sea bream, flounder...

831
00:43:19,846 --> 00:43:22,306
You must've been unfriendly.

832
00:43:23,126 --> 00:43:24,436
He likes to joke around.

833
00:43:24,436 --> 00:43:27,626
Working at a convenience store
was the hardest, but the most fun.

834
00:43:27,626 --> 00:43:29,646
- Really?
- It was like playing a game.

835
00:43:29,646 --> 00:43:31,486
- Convenience store tycoon.
- A tycoon game.

836
00:43:31,486 --> 00:43:33,876
Organize. Bam, bam, bam.

837
00:43:33,876 --> 00:43:35,276
I had a part-time job, too.

838
00:43:35,276 --> 00:43:37,816
I worked part-time at a wine bar.

839
00:43:37,816 --> 00:43:38,896
Really?

840
00:43:38,896 --> 00:43:43,796
I didn't know anything because I was young.

841
00:43:43,796 --> 00:43:45,606
People ask for a recommendation.

842
00:43:45,606 --> 00:43:49,916
I just picked a random one
and said it's tasty.

843
00:43:49,916 --> 00:43:53,346
- He's funny.
- I said, "This is dry and tasty."

844
00:43:53,346 --> 00:43:56,406
Everyone was satisfied once they tried.

845
00:43:56,406 --> 00:43:59,296
[Can't breathe]

846
00:43:59,296 --> 00:44:00,806
[Straight-faced]

847
00:44:03,096 --> 00:44:07,766
[The next dish is a pasta]

848
00:44:07,766 --> 00:44:11,356
- Wow, looks tasty.
- Primo Piatto.

849
00:44:12,246 --> 00:44:14,236
Today has been so great.

850
00:44:15,146 --> 00:44:16,606
Already?

851
00:44:16,606 --> 00:44:18,356
"Already?"

852
00:44:19,176 --> 00:44:21,636
- Already? He's funny.
- I like the way he throws it out there.

853
00:44:21,636 --> 00:44:24,236
- He's funny.
- He is funny.

854
00:44:24,236 --> 00:44:26,426
I liked the beginning.

855
00:44:26,426 --> 00:44:28,346
- Walking?
- Yes.

856
00:44:29,116 --> 00:44:31,286
I don't think that'd work.

857
00:44:34,096 --> 00:44:35,546
- Would you like this?
- He's peeling it for her.

858
00:44:35,546 --> 00:44:37,456
Thank you. I'll try it.

859
00:44:37,456 --> 00:44:39,586
[Yum]

860
00:44:39,586 --> 00:44:43,646
- I tried not to touch the flesh.
- It's okay.

861
00:44:44,416 --> 00:44:47,536
[He's quietly peeling another one]

862
00:44:47,536 --> 00:44:49,336
He's peeling everything for her.

863
00:44:49,336 --> 00:44:51,156
Thank you.

864
00:44:53,306 --> 00:44:55,336
Are you a caring type?

865
00:44:55,336 --> 00:44:58,076
Me? I think I am.

866
00:44:58,076 --> 00:45:01,266
Really? How unexpected.

867
00:45:02,406 --> 00:45:04,826
- Do I not look like it?
- No.

868
00:45:04,826 --> 00:45:07,746
How funny. They joke similarly.

869
00:45:09,056 --> 00:45:11,886
[Thinking]

870
00:45:11,886 --> 00:45:14,246
Have you gone through a period of confusion?

871
00:45:14,246 --> 00:45:18,506
- I think a lot of people go through it.
- Really?

872
00:45:21,706 --> 00:45:27,226
I usually think too much, but I try not to.

873
00:45:27,226 --> 00:45:29,456
I try to hold it in.

874
00:45:29,456 --> 00:45:31,406
Hold in the thoughts.

875
00:45:32,266 --> 00:45:35,936
- I try not to go too far.
- I think that's good.

876
00:45:35,936 --> 00:45:37,306
[Nodding]

877
00:45:38,276 --> 00:45:42,076
Something else might confuse me later.

878
00:45:42,076 --> 00:45:43,776
That could happen.

879
00:45:43,776 --> 00:45:45,086
Probably.

880
00:45:45,086 --> 00:45:47,856
[What will she be confused about?]

881
00:45:47,856 --> 00:45:51,296
Others might already be experiencing it.

882
00:45:53,526 --> 00:45:58,306
I'm scared.
I tend to get caught up in emotions.

883
00:45:59,736 --> 00:46:02,966
What kind of emotions?

884
00:46:02,966 --> 00:46:05,296
Happiness or sadness?

885
00:46:05,296 --> 00:46:07,106
Affected by happiness?

886
00:46:07,106 --> 00:46:10,716
Sadness? Disappointment?

887
00:46:11,766 --> 00:46:16,206
I mentioned that my feelings grow quickly.

888
00:46:16,206 --> 00:46:21,646
If I like someone this much,
I suffer the same amount.

889
00:46:21,646 --> 00:46:24,886
Isn't that usually how it is?

890
00:46:27,806 --> 00:46:30,136
So, you're afraid of that right now.

891
00:46:30,136 --> 00:46:32,576
Yes. I'm afraid.

892
00:46:35,296 --> 00:46:39,766
[Jun Hyeon has a lot to think about]

893
00:46:41,256 --> 00:46:43,186
It happens.

894
00:46:43,186 --> 00:46:47,316
But we need to see the end in a month.

895
00:46:48,416 --> 00:46:49,916
See the end in a month?

896
00:46:49,916 --> 00:46:53,226
We have to. How much longer...

897
00:46:53,226 --> 00:46:56,636
Do you think a month is long?

898
00:46:56,636 --> 00:46:58,846
- No.
- Right?

899
00:46:58,846 --> 00:47:00,156
I don't think it's long.

900
00:47:00,156 --> 00:47:05,496
I'm wondering what "the end" means. The end?

901
00:47:05,496 --> 00:47:07,836
What do you mean by that?

902
00:47:08,836 --> 00:47:12,976
The end of your feelings or...

903
00:47:12,976 --> 00:47:16,466
The other person, too? Both ways?

904
00:47:16,466 --> 00:47:19,006
You get to see the end if it's both ways.

905
00:47:19,006 --> 00:47:21,666
If not, I won't get to.

906
00:47:21,666 --> 00:47:24,546
I'm thinking it might not happen.

907
00:47:24,546 --> 00:47:26,116
That I might not see things through.

908
00:47:26,116 --> 00:47:29,656
Of course. It might not happen.

909
00:47:29,656 --> 00:47:33,126
But a month can be enough time.

910
00:47:33,126 --> 00:47:34,656
Wow.

911
00:47:39,686 --> 00:47:43,756
- Thank you.
- He's holding the door.

912
00:47:43,756 --> 00:47:46,966
He's cool. I suddenly find him charming.

913
00:47:48,566 --> 00:47:52,556
[Blood sugar spiking]

914
00:47:53,226 --> 00:47:56,446
The food must be making you sleepy.

915
00:47:58,446 --> 00:48:00,726
- What's this?
- It's a surprise.

916
00:48:00,726 --> 00:48:02,636
- What?
- Surprise?

917
00:48:02,636 --> 00:48:05,116
Are we going to a convenience store?

918
00:48:05,116 --> 00:48:08,196
[Jun Hyeon's prescription
for tired Yu Gyeong]

919
00:48:08,196 --> 00:48:09,946
Come here. Come here.

920
00:48:09,946 --> 00:48:11,936
This is the combo.

921
00:48:11,936 --> 00:48:13,646
Wow, daebak.

922
00:48:14,526 --> 00:48:19,686
[Adding a vitamin jelly to an energy drink]

923
00:48:19,686 --> 00:48:22,326
Gosh, daebak.

924
00:48:24,496 --> 00:48:26,076
It's perfect.

925
00:48:27,356 --> 00:48:29,616
He must've looked this up.

926
00:48:29,616 --> 00:48:31,126
This is a famous recipe.

927
00:48:31,126 --> 00:48:34,806
- Really?
- The jelly cocktail is trendy in Japan.

928
00:48:34,806 --> 00:48:37,046
He must've looked it up.

929
00:48:37,936 --> 00:48:40,446
Gosh, that's amazing.

930
00:48:43,986 --> 00:48:45,836
I love it.

931
00:48:45,836 --> 00:48:48,796
It's tasty, and it's waking me up.

932
00:48:49,646 --> 00:48:52,006
The jelly is the key.

933
00:48:53,186 --> 00:48:55,986
[Art museum]

934
00:48:55,986 --> 00:48:58,366
- They probably have something famous.
- They must.

935
00:48:58,366 --> 00:49:00,916
I love art museums.

936
00:49:00,916 --> 00:49:06,086
Wow, the staircase already looks grand.

937
00:49:06,086 --> 00:49:09,586
[Exciting art museum date]

938
00:49:09,586 --> 00:49:13,586
- Wow.
- Wow.

939
00:49:13,586 --> 00:49:15,436
[Otsuka Museum of Art]

940
00:49:15,436 --> 00:49:17,406
I've heard of this place.

941
00:49:17,406 --> 00:49:20,886
- It's a collection of famous murals.
- From other places.

942
00:49:20,886 --> 00:49:23,746
Daebak, what's this?

943
00:49:25,456 --> 00:49:27,426
So cool.

944
00:49:27,426 --> 00:49:29,676
This is crazy.

945
00:49:29,676 --> 00:49:33,216
[Getting sucked in]

946
00:49:33,216 --> 00:49:35,826
Wow, I like this room.

947
00:49:38,216 --> 00:49:41,016
This is the most famous sunflower painting.

948
00:49:41,016 --> 00:49:44,516
Wow, this is so Gogh.

949
00:49:44,516 --> 00:49:47,816
[Looking at "the Last Supper"]

950
00:49:47,816 --> 00:49:50,156
Did you watch "Infinite Challenge"?

951
00:49:50,156 --> 00:49:53,256
I did. I watched it a bit while growing up.

952
00:49:53,256 --> 00:49:58,406
- It's going viral these days.
- Right.

953
00:49:58,406 --> 00:50:01,696
This reminds me of that. I wondered
if you knew what it was.

954
00:50:01,696 --> 00:50:03,806
Of course, I do.

955
00:50:03,806 --> 00:50:06,796
That reminds him of "Infinite Challenge"?

956
00:50:06,796 --> 00:50:09,056
How does this make you feel?

957
00:50:09,936 --> 00:50:13,256
It makes me feel good.

958
00:50:13,256 --> 00:50:15,046
- This is so funny.
- What do you think?

959
00:50:15,046 --> 00:50:16,886
So cool.

960
00:50:18,726 --> 00:50:22,116
It's Monet. Water lilies.

961
00:50:22,876 --> 00:50:25,586
[A Monet replica]

962
00:50:25,586 --> 00:50:28,396
Daebak. So pretty.

963
00:50:29,626 --> 00:50:32,956
I like Monet's paintings.

964
00:50:32,956 --> 00:50:35,706
Should we count the water lilies?

965
00:50:35,706 --> 00:50:37,536
122.

966
00:50:43,086 --> 00:50:44,696
Are they both sleeping?

967
00:50:44,696 --> 00:50:47,266
- Seriously?
- They almost touched.

968
00:50:47,266 --> 00:50:50,666
How do you explain this situation?

969
00:50:50,666 --> 00:50:52,956
Did they agree to take a nap?

970
00:50:52,956 --> 00:50:55,146
- Klimt.
- Klimt.

971
00:50:56,646 --> 00:50:58,596
This is so...

972
00:51:00,296 --> 00:51:02,196
So cool. Klimt.

973
00:51:02,196 --> 00:51:07,736
[A painting caught his eye]

974
00:51:14,526 --> 00:51:19,086
[After the art museum date]

975
00:51:19,086 --> 00:51:22,546
[Heading to the next spot]

976
00:51:22,546 --> 00:51:25,526
[A French restaurant]

977
00:51:29,516 --> 00:51:31,856
Welcome. Come in.

978
00:51:34,226 --> 00:51:36,216
This is so nice.

979
00:51:36,216 --> 00:51:38,276
I know.

980
00:51:38,276 --> 00:51:43,826
It's sparkly outside, too.

981
00:51:43,826 --> 00:51:46,256
- This is so...
- How nice.

982
00:51:46,256 --> 00:51:48,256
Are you ready?

983
00:51:49,626 --> 00:51:54,136
[Cocktail-shaped appetizer]

984
00:51:54,136 --> 00:51:58,236
- Enjoy.
- Okay. These are veggies.

985
00:52:00,196 --> 00:52:01,826
It's tasty.

986
00:52:04,036 --> 00:52:11,586
When we ran into each other
in the house a few days ago...

987
00:52:11,586 --> 00:52:15,496
We talked a lot when we were in Yeongjong-do.

988
00:52:15,496 --> 00:52:17,396
Yes, we did.

989
00:52:17,396 --> 00:52:22,236
I think we stopped talking since then.

990
00:52:22,236 --> 00:52:23,996
I know.

991
00:52:27,426 --> 00:52:29,626
For many reasons.

992
00:52:29,626 --> 00:52:32,786
- Many reasons?
- There are many reasons.

993
00:52:33,636 --> 00:52:38,066
- It's because...
- Yu Gyeong has been preoccupied.

994
00:52:40,926 --> 00:52:43,736
It's not that I didn't want to.

995
00:52:43,736 --> 00:52:47,276
They're going to talk about themselves.

996
00:52:47,276 --> 00:52:52,416
I think it was the age gap.
Not because I'm older.

997
00:52:52,416 --> 00:52:59,976
I thought a young person should
date someone their age.

998
00:52:59,976 --> 00:53:03,226
That's just how I've always thought.

999
00:53:03,226 --> 00:53:05,626
He sure is an adult.

1000
00:53:09,886 --> 00:53:14,596
Do you prefer to talk formally?
You don't have to.

1001
00:53:14,596 --> 00:53:18,096
Let's... Let's talk casually.

1002
00:53:20,156 --> 00:53:22,826
To tell you the truth...

1003
00:53:24,026 --> 00:53:30,906
I haven't seriously considered you,

1004
00:53:30,906 --> 00:53:33,636
but I think I have subconsciously.

1005
00:53:35,676 --> 00:53:37,196
So...

1006
00:53:37,196 --> 00:53:40,146
[Hesitant]

1007
00:53:44,036 --> 00:53:47,436
Why am I rambling on? But...

1008
00:53:49,616 --> 00:53:52,236
I think...

1009
00:53:53,476 --> 00:53:57,486
I just think I've been...

1010
00:54:00,426 --> 00:54:04,356
noticing you the most. That's how I feel.

1011
00:54:04,356 --> 00:54:06,326
He's telling her. He's telling her right now.

1012
00:54:06,326 --> 00:54:08,186
He's honest.

1013
00:54:08,186 --> 00:54:12,696
[Without realizing,]

1014
00:54:12,696 --> 00:54:18,396
[he ends up expressing
his suppressed feelings]

1015
00:54:20,396 --> 00:54:22,356
What...

1016
00:54:22,356 --> 00:54:23,636
[Embarrassed]

1017
00:54:24,936 --> 00:54:27,806
But it's kind of...

1018
00:54:27,806 --> 00:54:30,756
I thought if I told you this today,

1019
00:54:32,206 --> 00:54:35,906
you might feel uncomfortable.

1020
00:54:35,906 --> 00:54:38,926
So, I thought I shouldn't have to.

1021
00:54:42,566 --> 00:54:46,876
But telling you doesn't change things much.

1022
00:54:47,886 --> 00:54:50,136
But if I had a concern,

1023
00:54:52,486 --> 00:54:58,586
it'd be that
I'm making you feel uncomfortable.

1024
00:54:58,586 --> 00:55:01,796
That would be the only thing.

1025
00:55:11,656 --> 00:55:16,376
I'm just telling you how I feel, honestly.

1026
00:55:16,376 --> 00:55:18,196
That's okay, right?

1027
00:55:20,476 --> 00:55:23,386
I feel like she can understand what he means.

1028
00:55:23,386 --> 00:55:33,836
[How does she feel after finding
out his true feelings?]

1029
00:55:33,836 --> 00:55:35,206
Wow.

1030
00:55:35,206 --> 00:55:36,756
Good job.

1031
00:55:36,756 --> 00:55:37,876
Did you rediscover Jun Hyeon?

1032
00:55:37,876 --> 00:55:39,136
- Totally.
- I certainly did.

1033
00:55:39,136 --> 00:55:42,636
He hasn't shown much interest in her.

1034
00:55:42,636 --> 00:55:45,766
There must be a reason
why he's telling her now.

1035
00:55:45,766 --> 00:55:49,276
I think it must've been the age gap.
Up until then,

1036
00:55:49,276 --> 00:55:51,296
he knew it was too big a gap.

1037
00:55:51,296 --> 00:55:58,346
And he always thought young people
should date someone their age.

1038
00:55:58,346 --> 00:56:01,316
"I've talked to the other three.

1039
00:56:01,316 --> 00:56:03,676
I tried to get to know all of them,

1040
00:56:03,676 --> 00:56:05,816
- but I'm still choosing you."
- Right.

1041
00:56:05,816 --> 00:56:07,876
That's a very impactful confession.

1042
00:56:07,876 --> 00:56:10,386
The fact that
he confessed his feelings honestly

1043
00:56:10,386 --> 00:56:12,206
might affect her a bit.

1044
00:56:12,206 --> 00:56:16,826
He tried to be honest without
making her uncomfortable.

1045
00:56:16,826 --> 00:56:21,046
I think she might find
his maturity attractive.

1046
00:56:21,046 --> 00:56:22,846
He became a potential love interest.

1047
00:56:22,846 --> 00:56:25,376
Right. You have to make yourself known.

1048
00:56:25,376 --> 00:56:30,966
It's like, "He likes me,
and I don't exactly dislike him."

1049
00:56:30,966 --> 00:56:36,196
She might start considering him, too.

1050
00:56:36,196 --> 00:56:39,616
- Wu Yeol and So Yun.
- Oh, my God.

1051
00:56:40,446 --> 00:56:43,566
- It's so analogue.
- I prefer this.

1052
00:56:43,566 --> 00:56:45,006
[Hehe]

1053
00:56:45,006 --> 00:56:47,886
- You know what I mean?
- Of course.

1054
00:56:47,886 --> 00:56:51,896
I'll do my best to serve you.
Thank you in advance.

1055
00:56:53,356 --> 00:56:55,706
[The driver is welcoming them
by using a translation app]

1056
00:56:55,706 --> 00:56:56,746
So cute.

1057
00:56:56,746 --> 00:56:59,176
[The date is starting off pleasantly]

1058
00:56:59,176 --> 00:57:02,126
- The streets are so pretty.
- I know.

1059
00:57:03,736 --> 00:57:06,636
I'll take a lot of photos of you.

1060
00:57:06,636 --> 00:57:08,796
I'll do the same.

1061
00:57:08,796 --> 00:57:12,276
I don't take a lot of photos because I'm shy.

1062
00:57:12,276 --> 00:57:15,176
But you made such a good model yesterday.

1063
00:57:15,176 --> 00:57:18,916
[Suspiciously photogenic man]

1064
00:57:18,916 --> 00:57:20,976
Wow, you look nice.

1065
00:57:21,806 --> 00:57:24,026
I was here yesterday.

1066
00:57:24,026 --> 00:57:26,856
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1067
00:57:26,856 --> 00:57:29,986
Your voice gets higher
when you speak Japanese.

1068
00:57:29,986 --> 00:57:32,366
Maybe it's because I'm cautious.

1069
00:57:35,236 --> 00:57:38,376
This is my first time in
a convenience store in Japan.

1070
00:57:38,376 --> 00:57:40,746
I want to buy a jelly.

1071
00:57:41,506 --> 00:57:43,516
That jelly of yours.

1072
00:57:45,046 --> 00:57:48,066
Let's get a few things.

1073
00:57:48,066 --> 00:57:51,596
- We should try a lot of food since we're here.
- Sounds good.

1074
00:57:52,426 --> 00:57:53,736
So nice.

1075
00:57:54,626 --> 00:57:56,266
Do you want deep-fried shrimp?

1076
00:57:56,266 --> 00:57:58,426
Deep-fried shrimp or tuna mayo.

1077
00:57:58,426 --> 00:58:00,576
I want tuna mayo, too.

1078
00:58:00,576 --> 00:58:02,616
Yes, this is it.

1079
00:58:03,486 --> 00:58:05,426
Two people.

1080
00:58:05,426 --> 00:58:06,676
[Entering the boarding area]

1081
00:58:06,676 --> 00:58:08,016
They still do it manually.

1082
00:58:08,016 --> 00:58:10,656
- Wow, so romantic.
- Thank you.

1083
00:58:11,466 --> 00:58:13,816
Thank you.

1084
00:58:15,346 --> 00:58:17,286
- Wow.
- This is so charming.

1085
00:58:17,286 --> 00:58:21,826
[A sweet and charming train station]

1086
00:58:24,896 --> 00:58:27,566
[Hands full]

1087
00:58:27,566 --> 00:58:29,736
I'll put your water in here.

1088
00:58:31,056 --> 00:58:33,086
Thank you.

1089
00:58:33,086 --> 00:58:37,416
I brought all the medicines just in case.

1090
00:58:39,486 --> 00:58:41,006
Want me to take a photo of you?

1091
00:58:41,006 --> 00:58:43,776
- No, no. Not yet.
- Not yet?

1092
00:58:50,656 --> 00:58:54,316
[Smiling]

1093
00:58:54,316 --> 00:58:56,436
[Glancing]

1094
00:58:59,906 --> 00:59:02,166
Do you need help carrying stuff?

1095
00:59:02,166 --> 00:59:05,246
I have a big bag. Give it to me.

1096
00:59:05,246 --> 00:59:06,786
Thank you.

1097
00:59:10,116 --> 00:59:10,806
[Looking]

1098
00:59:12,196 --> 00:59:15,376
This looks good. But you don't eat seafood.

1099
00:59:15,376 --> 00:59:18,186
Should we get mostly meat?

1100
00:59:18,186 --> 00:59:19,256
[Smiling]

1101
00:59:19,256 --> 00:59:21,446
She can't hide her feelings.

1102
00:59:23,526 --> 00:59:27,886
[The train is arriving just in time]

1103
00:59:40,756 --> 00:59:41,756
[Close]

1104
00:59:41,756 --> 00:59:43,316
They're close.

1105
00:59:43,316 --> 00:59:45,496
This will be fun.

1106
00:59:48,146 --> 00:59:52,456
Take a candid shot while doing
nothing. You know, right?

1107
00:59:52,456 --> 00:59:54,526
I can actually be good at it.

1108
00:59:56,846 --> 00:59:58,596
Here we go.

1109
01:00:02,556 --> 01:00:04,246
What? Taking a photo?

1110
01:00:04,246 --> 01:00:06,386
- What's this?
- Is it good?

1111
01:00:08,876 --> 01:00:10,796
[Fidgeting]

1112
01:00:13,276 --> 01:00:14,196
[Glancing]

1113
01:00:18,566 --> 01:00:20,506
I like the strap.

1114
01:00:21,846 --> 01:00:23,806
- Is it waterproof?
- Yes.

1115
01:00:23,806 --> 01:00:25,776
It's absorbent.

1116
01:00:29,756 --> 01:00:31,476
This is what I always wear.

1117
01:00:33,836 --> 01:00:34,746
[Brushing]

1118
01:00:40,016 --> 01:00:42,536
Were you signing up for classes on the plane?

1119
01:00:42,536 --> 01:00:43,976
How did you know?

1120
01:00:43,976 --> 01:00:46,766
How observant.

1121
01:00:46,766 --> 01:00:50,496
I tried not to let anyone see it.
I was embarrassed.

1122
01:00:50,496 --> 01:00:52,616
Everyone does it.

1123
01:00:55,466 --> 01:00:57,466
I didn't look too closely.

1124
01:00:58,756 --> 01:01:01,276
I saw you giving Yu Gyeong a massage.

1125
01:01:01,276 --> 01:01:02,596
She was watching everything.

1126
01:01:02,596 --> 01:01:07,096
[On the flight to Tokushima]

1127
01:01:18,526 --> 01:01:22,326
[Noticing]

1128
01:01:32,096 --> 01:01:34,126
I have a headache.

1129
01:01:38,476 --> 01:01:40,216
[Approaching]

1130
01:01:40,216 --> 01:01:42,026
[He massaged Yu Gyeong's stiff neck]

1131
01:01:42,026 --> 01:01:43,966
Why is your neck so thin?

1132
01:01:43,966 --> 01:01:45,376
[Glancing]

1133
01:01:51,426 --> 01:01:55,116
[Bothered]

1134
01:01:55,116 --> 01:01:56,866
I'll grab it.

1135
01:02:02,976 --> 01:02:05,066
Well...

1136
01:02:05,066 --> 01:02:08,996
- we both get headaches.
- Migraine?

1137
01:02:12,506 --> 01:02:17,426
Massaging this part helps.

1138
01:02:17,426 --> 01:02:19,306
Give me one sometime, too.

1139
01:02:19,306 --> 01:02:20,706
Gosh, of course.

1140
01:02:20,706 --> 01:02:22,026
Okay.

1141
01:02:25,746 --> 01:02:27,986
I'll use my elbow, then.

1142
01:02:33,026 --> 01:02:34,556
[Fidgeting]

1143
01:02:35,736 --> 01:02:38,526
I want to visit a studio.

1144
01:02:38,526 --> 01:02:41,276
- I'd like to buy a ring.
- A ring?

1145
01:02:41,276 --> 01:02:43,956
One for my index finger.

1146
01:02:43,956 --> 01:02:46,396
Right. Let's add a studio visit.

1147
01:02:46,396 --> 01:02:47,626
[Nodding]

1148
01:02:47,626 --> 01:02:50,576
I'm considering wearing jewelry again.

1149
01:02:50,576 --> 01:02:52,616
- I usually don't wear any.
- Me, neither.

1150
01:02:52,616 --> 01:02:56,896
But I want to get a ring made.

1151
01:02:56,896 --> 01:02:59,416
Are they getting matching rings?

1152
01:02:59,416 --> 01:03:01,876
[Staring]

1153
01:03:07,306 --> 01:03:08,506
Turn down the brightness slightly.

1154
01:03:08,506 --> 01:03:10,596
[So Yun's photography lesson?]

1155
01:03:13,596 --> 01:03:15,066
[Yum]

1156
01:03:16,936 --> 01:03:18,736
It's good.

1157
01:03:22,566 --> 01:03:24,766
- Isn't it good?
- Yes.

1158
01:03:24,766 --> 01:03:26,086
[A photo of him enjoying food]

1159
01:03:26,086 --> 01:03:29,116
She takes photos every chance she gets.

1160
01:03:29,116 --> 01:03:30,406
[Big bite]

1161
01:03:31,586 --> 01:03:33,126
I went, "Huh?" without realizing.

1162
01:03:33,126 --> 01:03:36,296
[Studying the route in advance]

1163
01:03:36,296 --> 01:03:38,656
- Should we eat this?
- Wow.

1164
01:03:38,656 --> 01:03:40,576
- Order everything.
- I'd love that.

1165
01:03:40,576 --> 01:03:42,406
Let's eat everything. This, too.

1166
01:03:42,406 --> 01:03:44,466
I found another romantic thing.

1167
01:03:44,466 --> 01:03:46,026
[Hehe]

1168
01:03:49,366 --> 01:03:51,356
[The train is passing an old residential area]

1169
01:03:51,356 --> 01:03:53,336
It's so pretty.

1170
01:03:54,806 --> 01:03:57,856
That's where locals live.

1171
01:03:57,856 --> 01:04:00,406
The weather is so nice over here.

1172
01:04:03,796 --> 01:04:05,156
- Halfway?
- Yes.

1173
01:04:05,156 --> 01:04:10,666
[Closing the blinds for her]

1174
01:04:14,186 --> 01:04:15,486
[Fidgeting]

1175
01:04:15,486 --> 01:04:18,186
[Staring]

1176
01:04:20,366 --> 01:04:22,726
Your eyes are wide open now.

1177
01:04:22,726 --> 01:04:24,326
Are you feeling better?

1178
01:04:26,806 --> 01:04:31,966
[The train arrives at the destination]

1179
01:04:35,526 --> 01:04:39,286
[What sort of things will happen here?]

1180
01:04:39,286 --> 01:04:40,596
Nice weather.

1181
01:04:40,596 --> 01:04:42,906
Isn't this a train track?

1182
01:04:42,906 --> 01:04:44,396
It is.

1183
01:04:45,216 --> 01:04:46,076
[Click]

1184
01:04:46,076 --> 01:04:47,236
[A photo to celebrate their arrival]

1185
01:04:47,236 --> 01:04:49,666
- They're like a Japanese couple.
- Looking good.

1186
01:04:49,666 --> 01:04:50,876
[Embarrassed]

1187
01:04:51,436 --> 01:04:52,886
[Working hard]

1188
01:04:52,886 --> 01:04:55,336
[With the train track background]

1189
01:04:55,336 --> 01:04:56,676
Aren't I good?

1190
01:04:56,676 --> 01:04:58,496
H-Hold on.

1191
01:04:58,496 --> 01:05:01,696
I didn't think you'd be so good.

1192
01:05:01,696 --> 01:05:03,826
The weather is nice.

1193
01:05:03,826 --> 01:05:07,966
We chose the perfect day.

1194
01:05:07,966 --> 01:05:11,636
- This is that place with the gate.
- You're right.

1195
01:05:11,636 --> 01:05:13,596
So pretty.

1196
01:05:13,596 --> 01:05:17,016
Gosh, it's so picturesque.

1197
01:05:21,176 --> 01:05:24,606
The streets are so pretty. And it's just us.

1198
01:05:24,606 --> 01:05:26,736
[Charming scenery in every street corner]

1199
01:05:26,736 --> 01:05:28,826
Even the breeze is perfect.

1200
01:05:29,826 --> 01:05:31,856
[What memories will they create here today?]

1201
01:05:32,366 --> 01:05:33,626
[Click]

1202
01:05:33,626 --> 01:05:35,376
- The shadow?
- Yes.

1203
01:05:36,156 --> 01:05:39,456
[Lovey-dovey shadows]

1204
01:05:41,096 --> 01:05:42,336
[Excited]

1205
01:05:42,336 --> 01:05:44,406
They make a nice couple.

1206
01:05:44,406 --> 01:05:45,956
Do you know this?

1207
01:05:45,956 --> 01:05:47,936
Of course, I do.

1208
01:05:49,256 --> 01:05:52,876
Wow, that's pretty nice.

1209
01:05:52,876 --> 01:05:54,726
This is it.

1210
01:05:54,726 --> 01:05:56,206
Here we are.

1211
01:05:56,966 --> 01:05:58,626
It's so nice.

1212
01:05:58,626 --> 01:05:59,976
[Amazed]

1213
01:05:59,976 --> 01:06:02,586
Gosh, it's so pretty.

1214
01:06:02,586 --> 01:06:05,266
Wow. Should we walk down the street?

1215
01:06:06,186 --> 01:06:08,696
- It's so nice.
- So nice.

1216
01:06:08,696 --> 01:06:10,866
- Wow.
- What? What is it?

1217
01:06:10,866 --> 01:06:13,706
- We saw this earlier.
- The phone booth?

1218
01:06:13,706 --> 01:06:14,746
[Embarrassed]

1219
01:06:14,746 --> 01:06:17,576
- I feel awkward.
- Do you?

1220
01:06:17,576 --> 01:06:18,546
[Smile]

1221
01:06:19,646 --> 01:06:22,086
Huh? I'm in it, too.

1222
01:06:23,316 --> 01:06:25,436
- Come here.
- Where?

1223
01:06:25,436 --> 01:06:28,266
[Their steps are lighter today]

1224
01:06:30,386 --> 01:06:32,616
I just took a nice one.

1225
01:06:32,616 --> 01:06:33,516
[Holding]

1226
01:06:33,516 --> 01:06:35,056
Why is my hand shaking?

1227
01:06:35,056 --> 01:06:36,826
Because you're nervous?

1228
01:06:37,976 --> 01:06:39,856
[Hehe]

1229
01:06:39,856 --> 01:06:41,696
Oh, this?

1230
01:06:42,556 --> 01:06:43,546
[V sign]

1231
01:06:43,546 --> 01:06:47,486
[Taking a couple of mirror selfies]

1232
01:06:48,336 --> 01:06:50,766
- It's a puppy.
- Where?

1233
01:06:50,766 --> 01:06:53,226
[A puppy on a walk]

1234
01:06:57,496 --> 01:07:00,676
[Sniff, sniff]

1235
01:07:00,676 --> 01:07:02,616
Huh? What's that?

1236
01:07:02,616 --> 01:07:06,186
Should we go there? What's it for?

1237
01:07:07,456 --> 01:07:09,026
Puppy.

1238
01:07:14,656 --> 01:07:18,836
[Wu Yeol can't stop looking at the puppy]

1239
01:07:18,836 --> 01:07:21,086
- So cute.
- It's like a Jindo.

1240
01:07:21,086 --> 01:07:22,296
It looks like a Shiba Inu.

1241
01:07:22,296 --> 01:07:25,046
[Focused]

1242
01:07:29,546 --> 01:07:32,556
[Sniff, sniff]

1243
01:07:36,426 --> 01:07:38,276
I want to go to trinket stores.

1244
01:07:38,276 --> 01:07:40,516
I don't know where it is.

1245
01:07:42,426 --> 01:07:44,256
- Is this it?
- Is it?

1246
01:07:44,256 --> 01:07:46,136
[Found a promising-looking shop]

1247
01:07:46,716 --> 01:07:48,436
Is this it?

1248
01:07:51,006 --> 01:07:55,016
[Filled with a lot of cute items]

1249
01:07:55,016 --> 01:07:56,496
Which one do you like the most?

1250
01:07:56,496 --> 01:07:59,576
- Accessories.
- It's fun to buy that stuff on a trip.

1251
01:07:59,576 --> 01:08:01,706
This suits you better
since your wrists are small.

1252
01:08:01,706 --> 01:08:03,486
- This?
- But this is too...

1253
01:08:03,486 --> 01:08:06,236
It's less stretchy, isn't it?

1254
01:08:06,236 --> 01:08:08,496
This looks stretchier.

1255
01:08:08,496 --> 01:08:10,116
You're right.

1256
01:08:10,116 --> 01:08:12,426
Try both.

1257
01:08:12,426 --> 01:08:14,576
You're smart.

1258
01:08:15,826 --> 01:08:18,516
This one? I think so, too.

1259
01:08:21,236 --> 01:08:23,466
I'll go with this one.

1260
01:08:23,466 --> 01:08:25,436
Rings?

1261
01:08:25,436 --> 01:08:26,986
Wow.

1262
01:08:26,986 --> 01:08:29,256
This isn't bad.

1263
01:08:31,006 --> 01:08:33,576
These are earrings, I think.

1264
01:08:33,576 --> 01:08:36,506
- Will you wear it here?
- It only fits here.

1265
01:08:36,506 --> 01:08:38,806
- It doesn't go in here.
- It's so pretty.

1266
01:08:38,806 --> 01:08:42,306
[So Yun is putting a ring on his finger]

1267
01:08:42,306 --> 01:08:46,236
- Is there only one?
- Here's one.

1268
01:08:46,236 --> 01:08:47,596
- Should I get this?
- Yes.

1269
01:08:47,596 --> 01:08:49,206
I'll get this.

1270
01:08:49,206 --> 01:08:51,646
- I love it.
- Are they the same?

1271
01:08:51,646 --> 01:08:54,206
It's the same, but there's only one left.

1272
01:08:55,196 --> 01:08:56,906
That makes me want to buy it.

1273
01:08:56,906 --> 01:08:58,776
This is so unique.

1274
01:08:58,776 --> 01:09:00,086
I'll buy it for you.

1275
01:09:00,086 --> 01:09:02,946
- What? No.
- No?

1276
01:09:02,946 --> 01:09:04,876
Do you want to buy it for me?

1277
01:09:07,036 --> 01:09:10,666
[Bought matching rings]

1278
01:09:11,556 --> 01:09:14,266
- I'll enjoy wearing it.
- A matching couple ring?

1279
01:09:14,266 --> 01:09:17,356
So pretty. Really pretty.

1280
01:09:17,356 --> 01:09:19,196
Come here.

1281
01:09:19,196 --> 01:09:21,316
Your hand, too.

1282
01:09:21,316 --> 01:09:25,156
[Photographing the rings they bought together]

1283
01:09:25,156 --> 01:09:26,176
- Like this?
- Yes.

1284
01:09:26,176 --> 01:09:28,606
- Hold on.
- Let's do it here.

1285
01:09:28,606 --> 01:09:32,246
- What's going on?
- Gosh, taking photos.

1286
01:09:32,246 --> 01:09:34,486
- So pretty.
- Do you like it?

1287
01:09:34,486 --> 01:09:36,316
I love it so much.

1288
01:09:39,456 --> 01:09:42,536
- I love it.
- So pretty.

1289
01:09:46,756 --> 01:09:49,156
It'd be bad if others found out.

1290
01:09:49,156 --> 01:09:51,486
A misunderstanding. It'd be a disaster.

1291
01:09:51,486 --> 01:09:55,296
- And So Yun will happily display it.
- Right.

1292
01:09:55,296 --> 01:09:57,426
I can't wait to see what happens
with those rings.

1293
01:09:57,426 --> 01:09:59,756
- I know. We'll find out.
- Even I'm nervous.

1294
01:09:59,756 --> 01:10:03,766
- How will they find out?
- Probably because of So Yun.

1295
01:10:06,486 --> 01:10:08,916
[Happy]

1296
01:10:12,016 --> 01:10:14,096
I want a coffee.

1297
01:10:14,096 --> 01:10:17,076
- Oh, my God.
- Should we get coffee, then?

1298
01:10:17,076 --> 01:10:18,996
It smells so good.

1299
01:10:20,246 --> 01:10:21,376
[Click]

1300
01:10:24,126 --> 01:10:24,796
[Hehe]

1301
01:10:24,796 --> 01:10:26,646
[Taking a photo of him taking a photo]

1302
01:10:28,566 --> 01:10:30,036
[Smiling]

1303
01:10:31,246 --> 01:10:35,026
I'm taking a photo because you're cute.

1304
01:10:41,056 --> 01:10:42,956
[Brushing]

1305
01:10:47,706 --> 01:10:51,306
Looks good. I'll turn on the translation app.

1306
01:10:52,736 --> 01:10:55,016
[Standing close]

1307
01:10:55,016 --> 01:10:57,156
Huh? Why do you keep following us?

1308
01:10:57,156 --> 01:10:58,386
[A cat is following them]

1309
01:10:58,386 --> 01:11:01,046
