1838
01:38:27,816 --> 01:38:30,566
Why are we talking like Shin-chan?

1839
01:38:33,506 --> 01:38:37,036
- Wow, delicious.
- Right, right?

1840
01:38:37,036 --> 01:38:38,886
Nice.

1841
01:38:41,396 --> 01:38:43,016
Yes...

1842
01:38:47,196 --> 01:38:49,916
It's nice, but time is passing by so quickly.

1843
01:38:49,916 --> 01:38:52,306
I know.

1844
01:38:52,306 --> 01:38:54,816
You know.

1845
01:38:54,816 --> 01:38:57,966
We talked about how we'd feel differently

1846
01:38:57,966 --> 01:39:00,896
once we're back from the trip.

1847
01:39:01,806 --> 01:39:05,536
Remember that Self Talk question?

1848
01:39:05,536 --> 01:39:07,606
How did you feel the past week?

1849
01:39:07,606 --> 01:39:09,686
So, how did you feel the past week?

1850
01:39:09,686 --> 01:39:13,236
After we come back from Japan...

1851
01:39:13,236 --> 01:39:15,586
I think...

1852
01:39:15,586 --> 01:39:17,936
Something will happen?

1853
01:39:17,936 --> 01:39:20,046
You said you'd feel differently.

1854
01:39:21,426 --> 01:39:23,586
I felt the same.

1855
01:39:24,546 --> 01:39:29,366
That we'd make long-lasting memories.

1856
01:39:29,366 --> 01:39:31,826
Seo Won is so sentimental.

1857
01:39:31,826 --> 01:39:34,986
[These two are deep in thought]

1858
01:39:36,206 --> 01:39:41,986
What will it feel like to return to the house?

1859
01:39:45,416 --> 01:39:46,306
[Glancing]

1860
01:39:48,396 --> 01:39:49,896
It feels strange, somehow.

1861
01:39:49,896 --> 01:39:53,536
Somehow... for some reason...

1862
01:39:54,666 --> 01:39:56,606
Strange for some reason.

1863
01:39:58,076 --> 01:40:00,176
That's how it is.

1864
01:40:00,176 --> 01:40:04,026
So strange. So many strange things.

1865
01:40:07,556 --> 01:40:11,896
[What are these two thinking about?]

1866
01:40:15,846 --> 01:40:18,826
Let's make sure we enjoy our last night here.

1867
01:40:19,836 --> 01:40:21,666
[Seo Won and Gyu were here!]

1868
01:40:22,756 --> 01:40:24,866
Gyu Ri is not totally unaffected.

1869
01:40:24,866 --> 01:40:27,286
She knows, of course.

1870
01:40:27,286 --> 01:40:29,036
It feels so different at night.

1871
01:40:29,036 --> 01:40:31,586
It feels like a cliff.

1872
01:40:31,586 --> 01:40:33,806
[Empty]

1873
01:40:34,456 --> 01:40:35,496
[Glancing]

1874
01:40:37,186 --> 01:40:38,136
[Blep]

1875
01:40:38,136 --> 01:40:41,196
[Copying her, as revenge]

1876
01:40:41,196 --> 01:40:43,396
I'm going to copy how you talk.

1877
01:40:43,396 --> 01:40:45,256
A positive sign?

1878
01:40:45,256 --> 01:40:47,956
So fun!

1879
01:40:47,956 --> 01:40:49,486
Make it sound dumber.

1880
01:40:49,486 --> 01:40:51,086
Dumber?

1881
01:40:51,086 --> 01:40:52,966
I love it...

1882
01:40:52,966 --> 01:40:54,146
[Giggling]

1883
01:40:54,146 --> 01:40:56,246
Gosh, I love this.

1884
01:40:56,246 --> 01:40:58,506
You get rid of random thoughts if you do that.

1885
01:40:58,506 --> 01:41:01,656
It'd be hilarious if we talked
the same way later.

1886
01:41:01,656 --> 01:41:04,406
- Go for it.
- I caught it from you.

1887
01:41:04,406 --> 01:41:06,726
I know...

1888
01:41:08,876 --> 01:41:11,226
Let's never forget.

1889
01:41:11,226 --> 01:41:13,746
Our memories in Japan...

1890
01:41:13,746 --> 01:41:16,826
Japan was too brief.

1891
01:41:16,826 --> 01:41:19,726
Too brief, seriously.

1892
01:41:20,916 --> 01:41:24,636
- My style.
- Seo Won really brought his charm.

1893
01:41:24,636 --> 01:41:27,666
- We're all into it.
- We are.

1894
01:41:27,666 --> 01:41:29,876
Totally. We're all Seo Won stans.

1895
01:41:29,876 --> 01:41:33,266
When Seo Won touched the hot alcohol lamp,

1896
01:41:33,266 --> 01:41:35,036
and said he'd rather get hurt.

1897
01:41:35,036 --> 01:41:38,256
- So cool.
- Is that how their relationship will grow?

1898
01:41:38,256 --> 01:41:39,836
That makes sense.

1899
01:41:39,836 --> 01:41:45,936
But did Seo Won get to Gyu Ri's heart?

1900
01:41:45,936 --> 01:41:48,266
- I think so. Because...
- He did?

1901
01:41:48,266 --> 01:41:53,336
Remember how she wanted to
speak formally and all that?

1902
01:41:53,336 --> 01:41:55,406
But she said being comfortable is important.

1903
01:41:55,406 --> 01:41:57,826
- Gyu Ri was eating so well.
- For the first time.

1904
01:41:57,826 --> 01:42:00,656
- She wasn't like that.
- We all saw it for the first time.

1905
01:42:00,656 --> 01:42:03,716
She needs to pick someone
she can be comfortable with.

1906
01:42:03,716 --> 01:42:07,056
I didn't make that choice in my twenties.

1907
01:42:07,056 --> 01:42:09,676
Right, it's hard to eat in front of your crush.

1908
01:42:09,676 --> 01:42:12,216
I was only into people who gave me stomachaches.

1909
01:42:12,216 --> 01:42:15,366
Someone who orders extra rice is the one.

1910
01:42:15,366 --> 01:42:17,006
Exactly.

1911
01:42:17,006 --> 01:42:18,746
I wonder what will happen when they get together.

1912
01:42:18,746 --> 01:42:23,296
I'm nervous. They've been so happy up till now.

1913
01:42:23,296 --> 01:42:24,396
Here?

1914
01:42:24,396 --> 01:42:27,416
- I'm curious about the ring.
- Yes, the ring.

1915
01:42:29,676 --> 01:42:31,466
Are we the first ones here?

1916
01:42:32,356 --> 01:42:33,816
What's going on?

1917
01:42:39,106 --> 01:42:39,876
[Cheers]

1918
01:42:43,456 --> 01:42:46,996
- This looks the best.
- Thank you.

1919
01:42:46,996 --> 01:42:49,126
- One more?
- Yes.

1920
01:42:49,126 --> 01:42:50,856
So cute.

1921
01:42:50,856 --> 01:42:53,446
[Jun Hyeon and Yu Gyeong arrive shortly after]

1922
01:42:53,966 --> 01:42:56,086
Hi.

1923
01:42:56,966 --> 01:42:58,166
When did you get here?

1924
01:42:58,166 --> 01:43:00,286
- It's just you two?
- Sit next to him.

1925
01:43:00,286 --> 01:43:02,176
We prepared this.

1926
01:43:02,176 --> 01:43:06,616
- Wow, how much did you order?
- She bothers So Yun.

1927
01:43:06,616 --> 01:43:08,796
- Others aren't here yet?
- Not yet.

1928
01:43:08,796 --> 01:43:11,586
- Didn't you eat dinner yet?
- We did.

1929
01:43:11,586 --> 01:43:14,246
We had four meals today.

1930
01:43:14,246 --> 01:43:16,166
- Four meals?
- We ate four meals.

1931
01:43:16,166 --> 01:43:17,836
Look at So Yun's face.

1932
01:43:17,836 --> 01:43:19,886
What did you do? Where did you go?

1933
01:43:19,886 --> 01:43:21,976
- Oh, there.
- Handkerchief.

1934
01:43:21,976 --> 01:43:24,126
Near here, right? Tokushima.

1935
01:43:24,126 --> 01:43:26,666
- Is it near here? We took a train.
- We rode on the train.

1936
01:43:26,666 --> 01:43:28,466
- An hour ride.
- Train trip?

1937
01:43:28,466 --> 01:43:33,086
- We walked the streets.
- It was a very quiet town.

1938
01:43:34,296 --> 01:43:38,386
- We visited shops.
- We walked around.

1939
01:43:38,386 --> 01:43:41,566
- Trinket stores.
- Right.

1940
01:43:41,566 --> 01:43:44,556
- Look.
- Wow, it's dyed.

1941
01:43:44,556 --> 01:43:46,736
- Ta-da.
- Are the colors matching?

1942
01:43:46,736 --> 01:43:48,436
This is the only color option.

1943
01:43:48,436 --> 01:43:50,176
A scarf...

1944
01:43:50,176 --> 01:43:52,306
You could choose.

1945
01:43:52,306 --> 01:43:54,526
It's a slightly different pattern.

1946
01:43:54,526 --> 01:43:56,806
- Pretty, right?
- It's nice.

1947
01:43:56,806 --> 01:43:58,796
It's a gradation.

1948
01:43:58,796 --> 01:43:59,976
Right.

1949
01:43:59,976 --> 01:44:01,366
[Reading the room]

1950
01:44:01,366 --> 01:44:03,046
Cute.

1951
01:44:07,016 --> 01:44:10,586
We wouldn't have shown you
if you'd reacted like this.

1952
01:44:10,586 --> 01:44:15,146
- I shouldn't have taken it out of my bag.
- It's nice.

1953
01:44:15,146 --> 01:44:18,426
[Seong Min and Min Ju arrive]

1954
01:44:18,426 --> 01:44:20,896
- Hi.
- Hi.

1955
01:44:24,066 --> 01:44:25,596
So warm.

1956
01:44:25,596 --> 01:44:27,716
We just had dinner.

1957
01:44:27,716 --> 01:44:29,326
What did you eat?

1958
01:44:30,136 --> 01:44:33,196
We went all out.

1959
01:44:33,196 --> 01:44:36,706
We had multiple-course meals all day.

1960
01:44:36,706 --> 01:44:39,056
So you're too full to eat this?

1961
01:44:39,056 --> 01:44:42,456
Definitely. Can't even look at it.

1962
01:44:44,036 --> 01:44:46,766
What about us?

1963
01:44:46,766 --> 01:44:48,436
About this kind of stuff...

1964
01:44:48,436 --> 01:44:51,366
[Jun Hyeon doesn't usually
speak up in group settings]

1965
01:44:51,366 --> 01:44:52,956
He's always been funny.

1966
01:44:52,956 --> 01:44:55,256
You can't beat our bike ride.

1967
01:44:55,256 --> 01:44:57,796
Gosh, come on.

1968
01:44:57,796 --> 01:44:59,886
You can ride back in Seoul.

1969
01:45:00,806 --> 01:45:03,006
No, no. It's on another level.

1970
01:45:03,006 --> 01:45:05,436
Sorry, but you could also eat
course meals in Seoul.

1971
01:45:05,436 --> 01:45:09,326
- It's different.
- Jun Hyeon can talk now.

1972
01:45:09,326 --> 01:45:13,036
It uses only ingredients unique
to Tokushima as its base.

1973
01:45:13,036 --> 01:45:16,376
Can't you just order it on a delivery app?

1974
01:45:16,376 --> 01:45:19,876
[They want to show off their date]

1975
01:45:19,876 --> 01:45:22,086
Look at them stare at each other.

1976
01:45:22,086 --> 01:45:24,086
Wow.

1977
01:45:24,086 --> 01:45:25,546
[The pizza you ordered is ready]

1978
01:45:25,546 --> 01:45:28,216
So much food.

1979
01:45:28,216 --> 01:45:31,046
- Wow, pizza looks delicious.
- I think I can eat.

1980
01:45:31,046 --> 01:45:32,496
[Glancing]

1981
01:45:32,496 --> 01:45:34,396
[Curious]

1982
01:45:35,296 --> 01:45:37,456
Do you want to eat pizza?

1983
01:45:37,456 --> 01:45:39,956
Want me to serve you a piece?

1984
01:45:43,936 --> 01:45:46,806
Or these.

1985
01:45:46,806 --> 01:45:48,826
[Yu Geong passes it instead of Wu Yeol]

1986
01:45:48,826 --> 01:45:50,796
Yu Gyeong passed it.

1987
01:45:51,706 --> 01:45:53,486
Delicious.

1988
01:45:53,486 --> 01:45:56,576
Didn't you all have dinner?

1989
01:45:56,576 --> 01:46:01,436
He even finished my leftovers.

1990
01:46:01,436 --> 01:46:04,736
Not to waste. So, I finished her leftovers.

1991
01:46:04,736 --> 01:46:07,476
What did you have for dinner?

1992
01:46:07,476 --> 01:46:11,326
- What was it? A chicken dish?
- Chicken...

1993
01:46:11,326 --> 01:46:14,686
- Sweet potato cheesecake, too.
- Right.

1994
01:46:14,686 --> 01:46:16,756
It was delicious.

1995
01:46:16,756 --> 01:46:19,366
- I was speechless.
- Was it next level?

1996
01:46:19,366 --> 01:46:20,956
Yes.

1997
01:46:22,806 --> 01:46:23,866
[Clocking it]

1998
01:46:25,806 --> 01:46:27,716
We had mochi.

1999
01:46:27,716 --> 01:46:30,146
Oh, mochi.

2000
01:46:31,726 --> 01:46:33,916
[Fidgeting]

2001
01:46:33,916 --> 01:46:37,096
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

2002
01:46:37,096 --> 01:46:41,426
[All eyes on the ring]

2003
01:46:41,426 --> 01:46:46,006
[Wu Yeol is wearing a ring, too]

2004
01:46:46,006 --> 01:46:47,356
Wu Yeol, what now?

2005
01:46:47,356 --> 01:46:50,916
She said she felt under the
weather because it was cold.

2006
01:46:50,916 --> 01:46:54,486
- What's she doing?
- Is she boasting it?

2007
01:46:55,976 --> 01:46:57,446
[Sees it]

2008
01:46:57,446 --> 01:47:01,436
She saw it! She saw it! She saw the ring!

2009
01:47:05,816 --> 01:47:09,166
[She can't help but notice]

2010
01:47:13,246 --> 01:47:16,596
The ring is so obvious.

2011
01:47:19,026 --> 01:47:22,246
Could I have a piece or two
of the warm wagyu?

2012
01:47:22,246 --> 01:47:24,616
Hey, but what's this?

2013
01:47:24,616 --> 01:47:27,046
Are you two wearing matching rings?

2014
01:47:27,046 --> 01:47:28,856
We got them at a trinket store.

2015
01:47:28,856 --> 01:47:31,586
So controversial.

2016
01:47:31,586 --> 01:47:33,586
Wait, I didn't see it.

2017
01:47:34,516 --> 01:47:37,106
- They're showing off.
- You're wearing rings?

2018
01:47:37,106 --> 01:47:38,786
Wearing rings?

2019
01:47:38,786 --> 01:47:41,716
There were only two left.

2020
01:47:41,716 --> 01:47:45,006
- What does that mean?
- She's not really smiling.

2021
01:47:45,006 --> 01:47:46,916
Rings?

2022
01:47:46,916 --> 01:47:48,976
Oh, rings... this is...

2023
01:47:48,976 --> 01:47:51,136
- What a statement.
- You went for it.

2024
01:47:51,136 --> 01:47:53,236
Should we go get four matching rings?

2025
01:47:53,236 --> 01:47:55,515
Let's look at where
they have four rings left.

2026
01:47:55,515 --> 01:47:56,706
I know.

2027
01:47:57,566 --> 01:47:59,746
You're wearing rings?

2028
01:47:59,746 --> 01:48:02,306
They can't say anything.

2029
01:48:03,996 --> 01:48:05,836
[Grinning]

2030
01:48:07,576 --> 01:48:08,686
I feel so warm.

2031
01:48:08,686 --> 01:48:10,176
[Licking her lips]

2032
01:48:15,406 --> 01:48:20,916
[She didn't hang out with Wu Yeol
the past two days in Japan]

2033
01:48:20,916 --> 01:48:22,286
[What happened during that time?]

2034
01:48:22,286 --> 01:48:26,606
Wu Yeol can't take off the ring
or leave it on now.

2035
01:48:28,426 --> 01:48:31,686
[Lastly, Seo Won and Gyu Ri arrive]

2036
01:48:32,246 --> 01:48:33,676
Hi.

2037
01:48:33,676 --> 01:48:36,196
What's all that stuff?

2038
01:48:37,146 --> 01:48:39,116
Hello.

2039
01:48:40,206 --> 01:48:42,086
Looks like you got a scarf.

2040
01:48:42,086 --> 01:48:43,856
How come you're so late?

2041
01:48:43,856 --> 01:48:46,026
Right? I told you!

2042
01:48:47,136 --> 01:48:48,486
- I knew it.
- Just as we expected.

2043
01:48:48,486 --> 01:48:51,256
We knew you'd say that first thing.

2044
01:48:51,256 --> 01:48:53,086
"How come you're so late?
What were you up to?"

2045
01:48:53,086 --> 01:48:55,136
I'd better hold back now.

2046
01:48:55,136 --> 01:48:57,226
- You got me.
- Wow, looks good.

2047
01:48:57,226 --> 01:49:00,266
Gyu Ri is there. Gyu Ri is surrounded.

2048
01:49:00,266 --> 01:49:03,036
- We've been here an hour.
- About an hour?

2049
01:49:03,036 --> 01:49:05,336
- That's quite a while.
- How was your date?

2050
01:49:05,336 --> 01:49:07,714
It was fun.

2051
01:49:07,714 --> 01:49:11,334
- The suspension bridge.
- We practically filmed "I Am a Natural Person."

2052
01:49:12,216 --> 01:49:13,796
We took like 3,000 photos.

2053
01:49:13,796 --> 01:49:15,306
3,000 photos?

2054
01:49:15,306 --> 01:49:18,876
- Just kidding.
- He's exaggerating.

2055
01:49:18,876 --> 01:49:21,286
We successfully crossed the suspension bridge

2056
01:49:21,286 --> 01:49:26,426
and got to see an incredible view
at the observation deck.

2057
01:49:26,426 --> 01:49:28,916
Is he hiding the ring?

2058
01:49:28,916 --> 01:49:30,696
How was your trip?

2059
01:49:30,696 --> 01:49:33,536
He must be restless.

2060
01:49:33,536 --> 01:49:35,776
[Steaming pasta looks delicious]

2061
01:49:36,746 --> 01:49:38,866
Try a little of this.

2062
01:49:38,866 --> 01:49:40,386
[Blowing]

2063
01:49:40,386 --> 01:49:43,276
[First, to Gyu Ri]

2064
01:49:44,206 --> 01:49:47,106
The noodles are so chewy.

2065
01:49:47,106 --> 01:49:48,536
Yeah.

2066
01:49:48,536 --> 01:49:50,836
It's like jjolmyeon*.
(Korean chewy noodles)

2067
01:49:53,056 --> 01:49:58,026
- I'm so happy. I'm happiness itself.
- Gyu Ri is much more relaxed.

2068
01:49:58,026 --> 01:49:59,796
Daebak.

2069
01:50:02,236 --> 01:50:05,236
What do you remember the most
from the museum?

2070
01:50:05,236 --> 01:50:06,786
One, two, three.

2071
01:50:06,786 --> 01:50:08,486
- Monet!
- Yes!

2072
01:50:08,486 --> 01:50:11,266
[Failed to sync up]

2073
01:50:11,266 --> 01:50:13,216
There's a separate Monet room at the museum.

2074
01:50:13,216 --> 01:50:14,536
How do you know that?

2075
01:50:14,536 --> 01:50:17,746
That's what it says here. Water Lilies.

2076
01:50:17,746 --> 01:50:21,186
He knew where to go.

2077
01:50:21,186 --> 01:50:23,376
It's all here. It was huge.

2078
01:50:23,376 --> 01:50:25,256
- How did you know?
- Right?

2079
01:50:25,256 --> 01:50:28,206
He's so smart.

2080
01:50:28,206 --> 01:50:29,776
He is smart.

2081
01:50:29,776 --> 01:50:31,506
I remember what he said earlier.

2082
01:50:31,506 --> 01:50:35,026
"Sunset is at 5:36 p.m."

2083
01:50:35,026 --> 01:50:37,906
We wanted to go for a bike ride
right at sunset.

2084
01:50:37,906 --> 01:50:39,606
So, I had 5:36 in my mind.

2085
01:50:39,606 --> 01:50:41,836
He's so detail-oriented.

2086
01:50:41,836 --> 01:50:43,586
It's a little exhausting.

2087
01:50:44,556 --> 01:50:48,196
Our trip was very "P."

2088
01:50:48,196 --> 01:50:52,196
"Wow, the view is so nice!" "I'm hungry."

2089
01:50:52,196 --> 01:50:53,296
[Cracking up]

2090
01:50:53,296 --> 01:50:54,956
Love it.

2091
01:50:54,956 --> 01:50:57,486
Love that.

2092
01:50:57,486 --> 01:51:00,916
We said, let's go for chicken and beer.

2093
01:51:00,916 --> 01:51:02,856
You become dumb next to the one you like.

2094
01:51:02,856 --> 01:51:04,436
We won.

2095
01:51:04,436 --> 01:51:07,896
She must be getting butterflies.

2096
01:51:07,896 --> 01:51:11,026
Wow, so delicious.

2097
01:51:11,026 --> 01:51:12,516
It looks delicious.

2098
01:51:12,516 --> 01:51:15,056
So delicious. Eat up.

2099
01:51:15,966 --> 01:51:18,336
So much to do in Japan.

2100
01:51:18,336 --> 01:51:19,926
So tasty.

2101
01:51:19,926 --> 01:51:23,776
It's almost like beef tartare. So rare.

2102
01:51:23,776 --> 01:51:24,966
[Glancing over]

2103
01:51:27,566 --> 01:51:29,616
Try this.

2104
01:51:30,796 --> 01:51:34,636
She's talking to Wu Yeol. Come on now.

2105
01:51:36,886 --> 01:51:39,906
What should I try? This?

2106
01:51:42,826 --> 01:51:44,646
Mmm.

2107
01:51:44,646 --> 01:51:46,246
Good, right?

2108
01:51:48,996 --> 01:51:52,636
It can't be tastier
than yesterday's yakitori...

2109
01:51:52,636 --> 01:51:56,936
She's bringing up yesterday.
She's reminding him of last night.

2110
01:51:56,936 --> 01:52:01,326
- I have high standards.
- Your standards are higher now.

2111
01:52:01,326 --> 01:52:04,296
We went to a super fancy place yesterday.

2112
01:52:04,296 --> 01:52:07,286
So Yun and her ring...

2113
01:52:07,286 --> 01:52:09,006
Sounds nice.

2114
01:52:14,856 --> 01:52:16,686
Oh, Seo Won...

2115
01:52:16,686 --> 01:52:20,496
We had no idea that
the place would be like that.

2116
01:52:20,496 --> 01:52:25,236
We weren't informed beforehand
yesterday. Right?

2117
01:52:26,696 --> 01:52:28,576
He must be jealous.

2118
01:52:28,576 --> 01:52:29,716
[Winking]

2119
01:52:29,716 --> 01:52:30,666
[Crinkling her nose]

2120
01:52:32,956 --> 01:52:34,716
What now?

2121
01:52:36,646 --> 01:52:39,706
We first got to a street
with lots of trinket stores.

2122
01:52:39,706 --> 01:52:43,576
But they were mostly furniture.

2123
01:52:43,576 --> 01:52:49,156
They weren't small items, but large ones.

2124
01:52:50,166 --> 01:52:52,986
We touched the cups.

2125
01:52:52,986 --> 01:52:55,506
We browsed baby items and sofas.

2126
01:52:55,506 --> 01:52:58,676
What? What did you do?

2127
01:52:58,676 --> 01:53:00,416
[Dizzy]

2128
01:53:00,416 --> 01:53:02,906
Seriously, what?

2129
01:53:02,906 --> 01:53:04,856
Baby items?

2130
01:53:04,856 --> 01:53:07,296
They must've thought you were newlyweds.

2131
01:53:07,296 --> 01:53:10,226
It was just there in front of us.

2132
01:53:12,926 --> 01:53:14,336
That was too much.

2133
01:53:14,336 --> 01:53:18,206
[Last night in Tokushima
is drawing to a close]

2134
01:53:18,206 --> 01:53:23,106
[Did you detect their heart signals?]

2135
01:53:23,106 --> 01:53:28,046
[Predict the eight people's
love lines based on clues!]

2136
01:53:28,046 --> 01:53:31,376
Texts? Today's texts? Wow...

2137
01:53:31,376 --> 01:53:33,996
Let's start with the easiest person.

2138
01:53:33,996 --> 01:53:35,926
I think today might be an easy day.

2139
01:53:35,926 --> 01:53:37,776
Who will be hard to guess?

2140
01:53:37,776 --> 01:53:40,086
All the dates were great.

2141
01:53:40,086 --> 01:53:42,506
- Min Ju is easy.
- Start with Min Ju?

2142
01:53:42,506 --> 01:53:45,086
Min Ju to Seong Min.

2143
01:53:45,086 --> 01:53:47,966
I bet Seong Min will also choose Min Ju today.

2144
01:53:47,966 --> 01:53:51,886
- They were so cute together.
- They were great.

2145
01:53:51,886 --> 01:53:54,176
You'll be mad if he chooses Yu Gyeong today, huh?

2146
01:53:54,176 --> 01:53:56,546
He didn't get a text from Yu Gyeong yesterday.

2147
01:53:56,546 --> 01:53:58,316
I agree.

2148
01:53:58,316 --> 01:54:00,806
I'm going to hold my tongue.

2149
01:54:00,806 --> 01:54:02,826
You don't need to agree.

2150
01:54:02,826 --> 01:54:05,506
- Since you did so badly last week.
- Do what you want. I'm out.

2151
01:54:05,506 --> 01:54:08,206
- But this week...
- Passionate love.

2152
01:54:08,206 --> 01:54:10,676
Park Wu Yeol and Choi So Yun. And vice versa.

2153
01:54:10,676 --> 01:54:13,366
I think they'll all choose their date today.

2154
01:54:13,366 --> 01:54:15,106
You never know.

2155
01:54:15,106 --> 01:54:16,986
Yakitori or ring?

2156
01:54:16,986 --> 01:54:18,376
Don't say that.

2157
01:54:18,376 --> 01:54:20,616
- I bet he'll choose Gyu Ri.
- Who did Wu Yeol choose yesterday?

2158
01:54:20,616 --> 01:54:22,846
[Canceling out Roy]

2159
01:54:22,846 --> 01:54:25,156
He chose Gyu Ri last time.

2160
01:54:25,156 --> 01:54:27,586
I say Gyu Ri. That's all.

2161
01:54:27,586 --> 01:54:29,936
- I think he'll choose Gyu Ri.
- Not today.

2162
01:54:29,936 --> 01:54:32,876
After today's date, he's lamenting
not going out with her today.

2163
01:54:32,876 --> 01:54:34,886
He asked if she'd choose him.

2164
01:54:34,886 --> 01:54:36,736
[Frustrated and disappointed]

2165
01:54:36,736 --> 01:54:39,536
- Just wait and see.
- We'll wait and see.

2166
01:54:39,536 --> 01:54:42,796
I told you. I won't try to convince you.

2167
01:54:42,796 --> 01:54:44,996
- I say So Yun today.
- Me, too.

2168
01:54:44,996 --> 01:54:47,096
- Same, So Yun.
- I say Gyu Ri.

2169
01:54:47,096 --> 01:54:49,846
Wu Yeol only thinks about what happened that day.

2170
01:54:49,846 --> 01:54:52,966
Roy Kim, let's wait and see.

2171
01:54:52,966 --> 01:54:54,806
Make sure you react fully.

2172
01:54:54,806 --> 01:54:56,776
I'll leave the show.

2173
01:54:56,776 --> 01:54:58,756
No, don't.

2174
01:54:58,756 --> 01:55:00,106
Get back in.

2175
01:55:00,106 --> 01:55:02,456
You make us look good.

2176
01:55:02,456 --> 01:55:05,596
Wu Yeol chooses So Yun. Fine.

2177
01:55:05,596 --> 01:55:08,896
Isn't this easy? So Yun for Wu Yeol, right?

2178
01:55:08,896 --> 01:55:11,336
[Can't forget about the ring]

2179
01:55:11,336 --> 01:55:14,556
- This is so...
- She spun it around and around.

2180
01:55:14,556 --> 01:55:17,266
- Today is simple.
- So simple.

2181
01:55:17,266 --> 01:55:18,706
Seo Won.

2182
01:55:18,706 --> 01:55:21,376
Gyu Ri, no question.

2183
01:55:21,376 --> 01:55:23,216
Gyu Ri will go for Seo Won, too, right?

2184
01:55:23,216 --> 01:55:25,726
They keep crinkling their faces at each other.

2185
01:55:25,726 --> 01:55:28,486
Winking, too.

2186
01:55:28,486 --> 01:55:30,746
They look good together.

2187
01:55:30,746 --> 01:55:32,486
The last thing she said, though.

2188
01:55:32,486 --> 01:55:33,866
Yakitori from last night.

2189
01:55:33,866 --> 01:55:37,086
[Summoned her memories
with Wu Yeol with that one line]

2190
01:55:37,086 --> 01:55:40,156
She's just reminding him of last night.

2191
01:55:40,156 --> 01:55:42,316
You're all oversimplifying it.

2192
01:55:42,316 --> 01:55:44,816
Let's make note of Roy's take.

2193
01:55:44,816 --> 01:55:46,526
It could be Wu Yeol.

2194
01:55:46,526 --> 01:55:48,996
- Noted.
- Okay, got it.

2195
01:55:48,996 --> 01:55:51,326
[His trustworthiness hit rock bottom]

2196
01:55:51,326 --> 01:55:54,816
What did I do to get to this point?

2197
01:55:54,816 --> 01:55:58,556
We'll say Seo Won.
But I think it could be Wu Yeol.

2198
01:55:58,556 --> 01:56:00,966
Don't say that.

2199
01:56:00,966 --> 01:56:02,396
Yu Gyeong.

2200
01:56:02,396 --> 01:56:04,996
Even Yu Gyeong is easy today.

2201
01:56:04,996 --> 01:56:09,016
- Yu Gyeong will choose Jun Hyeon, right?
- Sure.

2202
01:56:09,016 --> 01:56:11,726
All the dates were good today.

2203
01:56:11,726 --> 01:56:14,736
Let's go for a happy ending today.

2204
01:56:14,736 --> 01:56:17,456
Jun Hyeon is for Yu Gyeong, no question.

2205
01:56:17,456 --> 01:56:19,956
I think Jun Hyeon is set on Yu Gyeong.

2206
01:56:19,956 --> 01:56:22,036
So easy today.

2207
01:56:22,866 --> 01:56:24,676
That's all? Done?

2208
01:56:24,676 --> 01:56:26,596
What if we're wrong?

2209
01:56:26,596 --> 01:56:29,386
If we're right, we'll all score.

2210
01:56:29,386 --> 01:56:30,676
What a happy night.

2211
01:56:30,676 --> 01:56:33,006
- Scary.
- Please, please, please...

2212
01:56:33,006 --> 01:56:38,026
[Time to face their emotions again]

2213
01:56:40,466 --> 01:56:42,366
[Buzzing]

2214
01:56:42,366 --> 01:56:45,896
[Tired Camel: Sleep tight, don't get sick!]

2215
01:56:45,896 --> 01:56:48,826
That's right. A text from Tired Camel.

2216
01:56:48,826 --> 01:56:50,926
So meaningful.

2217
01:56:54,966 --> 01:56:56,216
[Beluga of the Forest: What a lucky and fun day]

2218
01:56:56,216 --> 01:56:57,686
Okay, okay.

2219
01:56:57,686 --> 01:56:59,586
Beluga says, "What a lucky and fun day."

2220
01:56:59,586 --> 01:57:04,216
[Beluga of the Forest]

2221
01:57:04,216 --> 01:57:08,016
He said, "Lucky." That sounds so nice.

2222
01:57:12,876 --> 01:57:15,436
[Busy Hamster: I'll never forget Tokushima!]

2223
01:57:15,436 --> 01:57:18,406
[Thanks for the memories,
and let's continue making them.]

2224
01:57:18,406 --> 01:57:20,286
[Stay healthy!]

2225
01:57:20,286 --> 01:57:21,776
[Busy Hamster]

2226
01:57:21,776 --> 01:57:25,046
- I feel at peace.
- I feel at peace today.

2227
01:57:26,036 --> 01:57:28,946
- They know each other's nicknames now.
- They do now.

2228
01:57:28,946 --> 01:57:29,896
[Smiling]

2229
01:57:29,896 --> 01:57:32,526
She's so happy.

2230
01:57:32,526 --> 01:57:37,316
[Wu Yeol, deep in thought]

2231
01:57:39,276 --> 01:57:42,386
So many conflicting feelings.

2232
01:57:45,626 --> 01:57:47,106
Is So Yun deep in thought, too?

2233
01:57:47,106 --> 01:57:49,936
She must be racking her brain, too.

2234
01:57:52,086 --> 01:57:55,736
- No way.
- I think it could be Gyu Ri.

2235
01:57:55,736 --> 01:57:56,796
[Salt Bread: Today was fun and thanks]

2236
01:57:56,796 --> 01:57:59,906
- "Today was fun and thanks."
- So simple.

2237
01:57:59,906 --> 01:58:04,236
[Salt Bread]

2238
01:58:08,416 --> 01:58:10,736
Is Gyu Ri expecting two?

2239
01:58:10,736 --> 01:58:13,416
- Sure.
- Same with Yu Gyeong.

2240
01:58:13,416 --> 01:58:15,816
They all might've expected two.

2241
01:58:20,946 --> 01:58:22,266
The bike.

2242
01:58:22,266 --> 01:58:23,656
[Buzzing]

2243
01:58:24,396 --> 01:58:26,666
[Sleepy Bear: Thanks for today]

2244
01:58:26,666 --> 01:58:28,366
"Thanks for today."

2245
01:58:28,366 --> 01:58:32,536
[Sleepy Bear]

2246
01:58:33,936 --> 01:58:37,766
[Pure Rabbit: Hope you remember
this Japan trip fondly]

2247
01:58:37,766 --> 01:58:39,086
There.

2248
01:58:39,086 --> 01:58:40,686
[Pure Rabbit]

2249
01:58:40,686 --> 01:58:43,266
Lord of the Rings.

2250
01:58:43,266 --> 01:58:46,856
So Yun is good at handling him.
She doesn't get dragged around.

2251
01:58:47,876 --> 01:58:52,256
[Who will Yu Gyeong choose?]

2252
01:58:57,556 --> 01:59:01,286
[My Dog, Yellow:
I hope you remember today fondly]

2253
01:59:01,286 --> 01:59:05,296
There you go. She went for Jun Hyeon.

2254
01:59:07,636 --> 01:59:09,356
[Plonk]

2255
01:59:10,916 --> 01:59:14,846
- Yu Gyeong still feels complicated.
- She's still hurting.

2256
01:59:18,256 --> 01:59:24,016
[Lastly, Gyu Ri's text]

2257
01:59:24,016 --> 01:59:25,906
Roy insisted on who Gyu Ri would choose.

2258
01:59:25,906 --> 01:59:28,536
[Gyu Ri can choose Wu Yeol]

2259
01:59:28,536 --> 01:59:30,976
- I'm nervous about Gyu Ri.
- Don't be.

2260
01:59:30,976 --> 01:59:33,006
Please...

2261
01:59:36,906 --> 01:59:39,406
He's eagerly awaiting.

2262
01:59:39,406 --> 01:59:42,426
- He's waiting.
- Cute.

2263
01:59:46,826 --> 01:59:50,336
[Dried Sweet Potato:
Let's enjoy the remaining time]

2264
01:59:51,156 --> 01:59:53,266
[Dried Sweet Potato]

2265
01:59:53,266 --> 01:59:55,636
Just be comfortable like that.

2266
01:59:57,036 --> 01:59:58,896
He's so giddy.

2267
01:59:58,896 --> 02:00:01,026
[Can't hide his smile]

2268
02:00:01,026 --> 02:00:05,836
We have successfully guessed
their love line choices!

2269
02:00:05,836 --> 02:00:08,706
- What a beautiful night!
- Very much so.

2270
02:00:08,706 --> 02:00:11,436
You know, I was serious.

2271
02:00:11,436 --> 02:00:14,836
- Were you really?
- I wasn't kidding. For real.

2272
02:00:14,836 --> 02:00:16,466
[Don't put on a show]

2273
02:00:16,466 --> 02:00:19,186
- Isn't it here?
- How exciting.

2274
02:00:19,186 --> 02:00:22,216
[Final stop before returning home]

2275
02:00:22,216 --> 02:00:25,476
[Dessert shop]

2276
02:00:25,476 --> 02:00:28,106
So pretty.

2277
02:00:28,106 --> 02:00:31,026
[Tokushima's luxury dessert, evoking emotion]

2278
02:00:31,026 --> 02:00:33,676
[Browning]

2279
02:00:34,246 --> 02:00:36,106
We can try them.

2280
02:00:36,106 --> 02:00:38,126
[Manju tasting corner]

2281
02:00:40,496 --> 02:00:43,036
Buy now. Pick them out, quick.

2282
02:00:43,036 --> 02:00:44,926
So good.

2283
02:00:44,926 --> 02:00:48,586
I'm going to get them for my two friends.

2284
02:00:48,586 --> 02:00:51,026
- For your two friends...
- I'm getting two.

2285
02:00:51,026 --> 02:00:52,306
So cute.

2286
02:00:52,306 --> 02:00:53,966
As a gift.

2287
02:00:53,966 --> 02:00:55,526
[Debating]

2288
02:00:57,266 --> 02:00:59,306
[Picking out...]

2289
02:00:59,306 --> 02:01:01,436
What's this?

2290
02:01:01,436 --> 02:01:04,416
[Picking out heartfelt gifts]

2291
02:01:04,416 --> 02:01:06,516
I'm running out of hands.

2292
02:01:06,516 --> 02:01:07,906
Wow...

2293
02:01:07,906 --> 02:01:10,236
[Organizing]

2294
02:01:10,236 --> 02:01:13,236
- I'll put some at the house.
- Love that.

2295
02:01:13,236 --> 02:01:16,276
We'll eat seaweed and ramen all day long.

2296
02:01:17,046 --> 02:01:20,346
- Who's done shopping?
- Me.

2297
02:01:20,346 --> 02:01:22,316
That was delicious.

2298
02:01:23,446 --> 02:01:27,856
It's something to carry
armfuls of shopping bags.

2299
02:01:28,856 --> 02:01:31,756
- We're back.
- We're back at the house.

2300
02:01:32,876 --> 02:01:35,146
[Lifting]

2301
02:01:35,916 --> 02:01:37,416
You're doing great. Go in.

2302
02:01:37,416 --> 02:01:39,986
I'm happy to be home.

2303
02:01:39,986 --> 02:01:41,736
It's nice.

2304
02:01:47,326 --> 02:01:50,186
[Remembering the promise]

2305
02:01:52,966 --> 02:01:55,096
[Gyu Ri is organizing the shoes]

2306
02:01:55,096 --> 02:01:57,666
You're just organizing, right?

2307
02:01:57,666 --> 02:01:59,336
- Organizing?
- Yes.

2308
02:01:59,336 --> 02:02:00,906
- Are you done?
- Yes.

2309
02:02:00,906 --> 02:02:04,556
[Hesitating]

2310
02:02:05,536 --> 02:02:07,106
Tomorrow?

2311
02:02:08,746 --> 02:02:13,776
[What will happen tomorrow?]

2312
02:02:14,336 --> 02:02:20,376
How does it feel when your crush
is into someone else?

2313
02:02:21,416 --> 02:02:23,016
I'm going for Wu Yeol.

2314
02:02:23,016 --> 02:02:24,926
What are you guys doing in secret?

2315
02:02:24,926 --> 02:02:26,796
What are you doing tomorrow?

2316
02:02:26,796 --> 02:02:31,946
I think it'd be better to muster up
the courage and share how we feel.

2317
02:02:31,946 --> 02:02:35,316
Do you have any plans? Are you free?

2318
02:02:37,086 --> 02:02:39,316
Promise.

2319
02:02:39,316 --> 02:02:41,846
I wanted to spend the weekend with you again.

2320
02:02:41,846 --> 02:02:44,506
I could tell.

2321
02:02:44,506 --> 02:02:47,026
- I feel bad.
- About what?

2322
02:02:47,026 --> 02:02:49,886
I don't regret the choices I made.

2323
02:02:49,886 --> 02:02:52,916
If you're willing to come to me...

2324
02:02:54,986 --> 02:02:57,506
I would love that.

2325
02:02:58,826 --> 02:03:01,536
Love it.

2326
02:03:01,536 --> 02:03:04,416
I have no idea how you feel.

2327
02:03:07,136 --> 02:03:09,716
Thank you.

2328
02:03:09,716 --> 02:03:11,876
Can't you see me?

2329
02:03:13,276 --> 02:03:16,716
It'd be nice to catch a movie together.

2330
02:03:18,926 --> 02:03:20,906
So soon?

2331
02:03:22,986 --> 02:03:26,456
Let's go watch a movie sometime.

2332
02:03:27,596 --> 02:03:29,256
I'd like that.
